WEBVTT

01:34.712 --> 01:37.089
Bro! Excuse me! Sorry.

01:51.186 --> 01:52.396
Left.

02:18.047 --> 02:21.300
Stop sign, left.

02:43.530 --> 02:50.537
One, two, three, four, five.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.582
On the right.

03:09.264 --> 03:10.099
Mr. Burnz?

03:11.141 --> 03:12.976
Are you Charlie Burnz?

03:13.894 --> 03:15.813
Charlie Burnz, I'm talking to you.

03:16.855 --> 03:18.899
Mr. Burnz, Charlie Burnz.

03:38.043 --> 03:41.797
Sweep up a little bit. Make sure
all the props are in the right spot.

03:41.880 --> 03:44.133
- Hey, Marge?
- Hey, Charlie.

03:44.216 --> 03:45.342
Where is everybody?

03:46.301 --> 03:49.930
Charlie, it's Monday.
They're at the writers' meeting.

03:50.014 --> 03:54.268
Oh, right. Well, I had a long weekend.

03:54.351 --> 03:56.437
All right, take it easy. All right.

03:56.520 --> 03:59.398
Better hurry.
They're pitching new sketches!

03:59.481 --> 04:01.525
Yeah, we made sure to take a lot of care

04:01.608 --> 04:04.695
and not offend anybody
with this next sketch, so please strap in

04:04.778 --> 04:06.405
and, you know, enjoy.

04:06.488 --> 04:07.406
Okay, so this is...

04:07.489 --> 04:10.075
This is an infomercial
for a brand-new comedy album.

04:10.159 --> 04:14.455
We start with shots of planets and stars,
just these beautiful shots of space.

04:14.538 --> 04:17.623
And then, we hear a VO,
and we see a chyron.

04:17.707 --> 04:20.544
In the tradition of George Carlin
and Richard Pryor,

04:20.627 --> 04:22.504
we bring you the next comedy voice.

04:22.588 --> 04:25.841
And we cut to a photograph
of Stephen Hawking.

04:27.468 --> 04:29.928
But we photoshopped him
in front of a brick wall.

04:30.012 --> 04:31.805
So he looks like he's at a comedy club.

04:31.889 --> 04:33.849
We have a microphone
where his computer is.

04:35.059 --> 04:41.398
Is it just me, but what's the deal
with black holes? Am I right?

04:44.193 --> 04:47.029
You people like impressions?

04:54.495 --> 04:56.080
So how do you think the meeting went?

04:58.040 --> 04:59.792
Some very funny ideas.

04:59.875 --> 05:04.171
But, Brad, somebody's got to talk
to Roger about his inflections.

05:04.254 --> 05:06.340
I know, I know. I think he gets nervous.

05:06.423 --> 05:07.591
No, come on.

05:07.675 --> 05:09.718
George Carlin, Richard Pryor.

05:09.802 --> 05:13.847
My God, Stephen Hawking pronounced
his name better than he does.

05:13.931 --> 05:15.474
Here's one for the news segment.

05:15.557 --> 05:18.435
Or as Roger calls it, the news "seg-ment."

05:18.519 --> 05:20.396
All right, I'll give this to the guys.

05:20.479 --> 05:22.690
By the way, there's a new invention
called computers.

05:22.773 --> 05:24.108
You may wanna get one.

05:24.191 --> 05:26.694
You know, I had one, but I like this.

05:26.777 --> 05:29.071
We started out together.
I love the feel of the paper.

05:29.154 --> 05:33.033
I like the fact that the key leaves a mark
that wasn't there a second ago.

05:33.117 --> 05:35.911
But I did treat myself to one of these.

05:36.912 --> 05:38.497
Look at you. You know how to work it?

05:38.580 --> 05:41.709
Absolutely, unless I wanna send an e-mail,
a text, or make a phone call.

05:41.792 --> 05:43.544
- Oh, that's not important.
- Not at all.

05:43.627 --> 05:46.255
- Wanna get something to eat?
- I have a lunch date.

05:46.338 --> 05:47.965
Look at you, Mr. Social.

05:48.048 --> 05:51.135
It's someone who won an auction
to have lunch with me at the charity event

05:51.218 --> 05:52.803
for inner-city libraries.

05:52.886 --> 05:53.929
Sounds like a blast.

06:01.395 --> 06:03.981
This restaurant nice. Excuse me.

06:04.481 --> 06:05.858
Oh, no.

06:06.233 --> 06:07.985
Sorry. Bye.

06:08.068 --> 06:10.446
Maybe you, sir. Hello.

06:10.529 --> 06:14.491
Oh, Phil Donahue. Nice to meet you.

06:14.575 --> 06:18.454
- The hell was that all about?
- Sir, hi.

06:18.537 --> 06:21.707
Oh, no, sorry, sorry to bother you.
Wrong person.

06:21.790 --> 06:23.459
Excuse me. Bye-bye.

06:24.126 --> 06:27.212
Excuse me. Are you, by any chance,
looking for me?

06:27.296 --> 06:28.547
I'm Charlie Burnz.

06:28.630 --> 06:30.341
- You gotta be shitting me.
- What?

06:30.424 --> 06:31.425
This was you?

06:31.508 --> 06:33.344
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:33.427 --> 06:35.262
You took some hits along the way, huh?

06:35.346 --> 06:37.848
Yeah, you might say that,
but that's a very old picture.

06:37.931 --> 06:41.352
That was actually taken on the <i>Mayflower.</i>
I did win the shuffleboard tournament.

06:42.394 --> 06:45.689
Well, belated congratulations.
I'm Emma Payge.

06:45.773 --> 06:47.816
- Emma, pleasure, thank you. Sit down.
- Sorry I'm late.

06:47.900 --> 06:51.070
Don't worry about it. Not a problem.
Glad you're here.

06:51.153 --> 06:53.197
And thank you for bidding
on me at the auction.

06:53.280 --> 06:56.075
I'm so flattered that somebody your age
would be a fan of my work.

06:57.034 --> 06:58.827
- Truth?
- Sure.

06:58.911 --> 07:00.913
I don't know who the hell you are.

07:01.205 --> 07:02.956
My ex bid on you.

07:03.040 --> 07:04.583
- You didn't?
- Nope.

07:05.584 --> 07:06.752
How did this...?

07:06.835 --> 07:09.088
Well, he's an actor,
and he was doing a scene

07:09.171 --> 07:10.964
from one of your plays
in his acting class,

07:11.048 --> 07:12.800
and he wanted to meet you,
so he bid.

07:14.259 --> 07:16.053
- How much?
- Twenty-two.

07:16.136 --> 07:20.391
- $2200? That's fantastic.
- $2200, my ass!

07:20.474 --> 07:22.351
$22.

07:22.434 --> 07:24.853
$22 was the winning bid?

07:25.979 --> 07:29.858
It started at 20, and then it went up
in 50-cent increments.

07:29.942 --> 07:32.194
Oh, that's so sad.

07:32.277 --> 07:34.988
Hello. Welcome to Le Monde.

07:35.072 --> 07:37.199
I'll be your server.
What can I get for you?

07:37.282 --> 07:38.659
- Have you eaten here before?
- No.

07:38.742 --> 07:42.579
They have the greatest steak sandwich.
That's all I get. It's fantastic.

07:42.663 --> 07:44.707
That's perfect.
I'll have the seafood salad.

07:46.500 --> 07:49.461
- Okay. And for you, sir?
- I'm gonna have the...

07:49.545 --> 07:53.841
Oh, can I have extra clams,
extra calamari, and extra crab meat?

07:54.842 --> 07:57.428
- Of course. And for you, sir?
- I'm gonna have the...

07:57.511 --> 08:01.557
Oh, and can I have a lobster tail
right on top, with extra mussels?

08:01.640 --> 08:02.641
Lots of mussels.

08:02.725 --> 08:05.811
The ones from New Zealand, not from Jersey
because they got black hairs.

08:05.894 --> 08:08.355
Who knows what's in those?
That can be really toxic.

08:08.439 --> 08:11.984
Are you done? Because there are
a few species you haven't mentioned yet.

08:12.568 --> 08:13.569
Go ahead.

08:13.652 --> 08:16.572
- I'm gonna have the...
- Oh, can I have a Diet Coke?

08:17.656 --> 08:19.408
And for you, sir?

08:19.491 --> 08:22.619
I'm gonna have a tuna sandwich,
whole wheat toast, and an iced tea.

08:22.703 --> 08:25.164
Very good.

08:25.998 --> 08:28.375
Why would you order a tuna sandwich
when you said

08:28.459 --> 08:30.127
they had the best steak sandwiches?

08:30.210 --> 08:32.504
While you were ordering half
of the Atlantic Ocean,

08:32.588 --> 08:35.758
I developed a hankering
for the only fish left on the menu.

08:36.342 --> 08:39.177
Touché, old man. Touché.

08:39.927 --> 08:41.180
So let me ask you a question.

08:41.263 --> 08:43.640
If you don't know who I am,
how come your ex didn't come?

08:44.224 --> 08:45.934
I caught him cheating on me.

08:46.018 --> 08:49.438
And he said it was because
I'm the worst lay in the world.

08:49.521 --> 08:52.566
And trust me, he is wrong, okay?

08:52.649 --> 08:56.028
You ought to see my moves.
It's "Circus Doleil."

08:56.737 --> 08:59.448
Okay. Well, let's...
Let's get through lunch first.

09:00.074 --> 09:02.326
- I'd break your back, old man.
- Thank you.

09:02.409 --> 09:05.496
Yeah, have you laid out, dead,
with a smile on your face.

09:06.205 --> 09:10.125
And your kids will be like,
"How did he die? How did my dad die?"

09:10.209 --> 09:12.795
And I would just look at them
in their eyes and say,

09:12.878 --> 09:13.921
on top of me.

09:17.883 --> 09:19.426
That's a really lovely thought.

09:20.678 --> 09:22.971
You funny, old man.

09:23.055 --> 09:27.726
I'm glad I came, even if it was
to shove you up my ex's big fat ass.

09:27.810 --> 09:30.104
Now, there's a compliment
you don't hear every day.

09:31.605 --> 09:34.441
- Whoa, look what the tide brought in.
- Yeah.

09:34.525 --> 09:36.610
- Thank you very much.
- Please enjoy.

09:36.694 --> 09:38.570
Emma, enjoy your buffet.

09:39.113 --> 09:42.533
So... I take it you like comedy.

09:43.325 --> 09:44.284
Nope.

09:44.368 --> 09:45.703
You don't?

09:45.786 --> 09:49.456
I mean, I love to laugh, but in real life.
You know what I'm saying?

09:50.249 --> 09:53.961
Well, you know, that's what I do
in real life. I'm a comedy writer.

09:54.044 --> 09:56.505
You ever watch <i>This Just In</i>
on Sunday nights on Funny?

09:58.424 --> 10:02.720
I also write some Broadway and movies
and five books.

10:03.721 --> 10:05.723
And what do you do?

10:05.806 --> 10:09.351
Charlie, I don't feel so good.

10:09.435 --> 10:11.729
Why is your face suddenly bigger
than it was before?

10:11.812 --> 10:15.858
- I can't feel my lips.
- Oh, are you allergic to seafood?

10:15.941 --> 10:17.443
Oh, shit, maybe I am.

10:17.526 --> 10:18.610
What should I do?

10:18.694 --> 10:21.947
- Call the hospital. Call the hospital!
- What? What?

10:22.031 --> 10:23.657
Call the hospital!

10:24.533 --> 10:27.036
Dial the nearest hospital!
Dial the nearest hospital!

10:27.119 --> 10:29.038
<i>I do not know. Let me check the Web.</i>

10:29.121 --> 10:31.332
- Dial the nearest hospital!
- Is everything all right?

10:31.415 --> 10:34.084
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Okay, what did you do?

10:34.168 --> 10:35.085
I didn't do anything!

10:35.169 --> 10:36.337
These are Jersey mussels!

10:36.420 --> 10:38.630
- What?
- I knew they were Jersey mussels!

10:38.714 --> 10:41.550
- Jersey? No! I'm from Jersey.
- I need emergency. Emergency.

10:41.633 --> 10:42.634
This is an emergency.

10:45.095 --> 10:46.930
Everybody, calm down. Everybody, relax.

10:47.014 --> 10:50.642
- We should call the ambulance.
- Siri! What is wrong with you?

10:51.435 --> 10:54.021
Ma'am, have you had an allergic reaction
to seafood before?

10:54.855 --> 10:57.066
You just randomly ordered,
and this is what happened?

10:57.149 --> 11:01.403
- I had a hankering.
- Okay, just relax. We're almost there.

11:01.487 --> 11:03.197
You're gonna be okay.

11:03.280 --> 11:05.491
Charlie? Charlie.

11:05.574 --> 11:08.619
Charlie!

11:08.702 --> 11:12.414
You're all I've got, Charlie,
don't leave me!

11:29.306 --> 11:30.516
Oh, boy.

11:32.851 --> 11:34.645
Mr. Burnz?

11:36.689 --> 11:38.857
Oh, I'm not supposed
to fill these forms out.

11:38.941 --> 11:41.819
- What's your relation to Miss Payge?
- She won me in an auction.

11:43.362 --> 11:44.530
Fine, don't believe me.

11:44.613 --> 11:45.864
She doesn't have insurance,

11:45.948 --> 11:48.575
and she really shouldn't be leaving here
by herself.

11:48.659 --> 11:50.202
No insurance?

11:50.285 --> 11:51.745
Okay.

11:51.829 --> 11:53.330
$1100?

11:53.956 --> 11:56.375
Yes. And you'll get the ambulance bill
in the mail.

11:57.418 --> 11:59.211
You can pay me on the way out.

11:59.795 --> 12:02.381
- Your daughter is going to be fine.
- My d...?

12:02.464 --> 12:04.341
Great. Isn't that great?

12:04.425 --> 12:08.053
She told me all about how you adopted her
from that orphanage in Kenya.

12:08.137 --> 12:09.930
- That's very special.
- Oh, she told you?

12:10.014 --> 12:11.890
- Yeah.
- Yeah, well...

12:11.974 --> 12:14.309
Well, she is special.

12:14.393 --> 12:16.103
Well, this is a pretty severe reaction.

12:16.186 --> 12:18.313
Are there other allergies
that I should know about?

12:18.397 --> 12:20.649
Well, I think really you should talk
to her about that

12:20.733 --> 12:24.111
or I can put you in touch
with one of the elders of her tribe.

12:24.194 --> 12:26.739
You could ask for Mbolo.

12:27.740 --> 12:29.867
It's good that you reacted
as quickly as you did.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.952
A little longer
may have been a different story.

12:32.036 --> 12:34.038
Here are her prescriptions.

12:34.121 --> 12:35.998
Pharmacy is that way.

12:39.668 --> 12:41.128
$600?

12:42.838 --> 12:45.007
So far, a tuna sandwich
cost me close to two grand.

12:45.090 --> 12:47.801
- Welcome to New York, pal.
- What's this?

12:47.885 --> 12:50.471
That's epinephrine.
You need to inject her within the hour.

12:50.554 --> 12:52.056
- And if I don't?
- She'll die.

12:53.057 --> 12:54.058
Next.

12:55.893 --> 13:01.857
"Remove blue safety release
by pulling up, straight up."

13:01.940 --> 13:04.026
- Okay.
- What's taking so long?

13:04.109 --> 13:06.653
I'm having trouble reading the directions
without my glasses.

13:06.737 --> 13:09.114
And honestly,
I'm a little nervous about it.

13:09.198 --> 13:10.324
- Okay.
- Oh, no.

13:10.407 --> 13:12.743
Hell, no. Put that thing down.

13:12.826 --> 13:15.621
Ain't no way in hell I'm gonna let you
stab me with that Lego stick

13:15.704 --> 13:18.666
while your hand shaking like that.
You might put out one of my eyes.

13:18.749 --> 13:21.710
But they said I have to do it
within the hour or you'll be in trouble.

13:21.794 --> 13:24.630
Well, we'll just wait an hour.
If I'm not dead, you can go home.

13:24.713 --> 13:26.715
Fine. Enjoy your bloating.

13:29.635 --> 13:31.887
All right. Stick me, old man.

13:40.646 --> 13:41.897
Motherf...!

13:43.357 --> 13:44.775
Son of a...!

13:46.402 --> 13:47.319
Okay.

13:47.403 --> 13:49.488
Show time's over.

13:51.240 --> 13:53.742
Make me some tea, maybe it'll
help with the bloating...

13:53.826 --> 13:56.745
"Only hold in for a few seconds."

14:03.752 --> 14:05.087
"Slippery when wet?"

14:05.170 --> 14:07.297
- You looked?
- I had to. I really...

14:07.381 --> 14:10.843
I had to. That's not something you wanna
do with your eyes closed. Believe me.

14:10.926 --> 14:13.846
It could have ended up someplace
that we would not be happy about.

14:15.514 --> 14:19.727
Thank you. I promise I will pay you back
every dime that you laid out.

14:19.810 --> 14:21.937
You don't have to do that.
How are you feeling?

14:22.021 --> 14:24.440
Like you shot me up
with five six-hour energy drinks.

14:24.523 --> 14:27.776
So I've got about a good 30 hours
of energy! I'm lit!

14:29.486 --> 14:31.405
- Can I ask you something?
- What?

14:31.488 --> 14:33.323
Why did you tell the doctor
that I was your father?

14:33.407 --> 14:36.076
I thought it would be cool
to have a white dad.

14:36.160 --> 14:38.287
And the orphanage story?

14:38.370 --> 14:39.872
I was a little loopy by then.

14:39.955 --> 14:41.665
I'm sure that was the mussels talking.

14:41.749 --> 14:43.667
Yup, those mussels
were definitely talking.

14:43.751 --> 14:45.586
Yeah, must have been.

14:45.669 --> 14:48.339
Well, listen, try to get some rest.

14:48.422 --> 14:50.507
Do you need anything else?
I have 20 bucks left.

14:51.967 --> 14:53.135
I'll be fine.

14:53.218 --> 14:56.597
Look, I wanna apologize to you
for saying all that stuff about my ex.

14:56.680 --> 14:58.223
I should have never done that.

14:58.307 --> 15:01.018
You are a good man,
and that was not fair to you.

15:01.101 --> 15:04.355
- Hey, I understand. This way out?
- Yep, that way.

15:05.814 --> 15:07.232
- Perky.
- Yeah.

15:19.453 --> 15:20.579
Good try.

15:23.374 --> 15:25.876
- All right, that's...
- It's all right. It's a base hit.

15:36.011 --> 15:37.930
Sorry, Rex. That's a match.

15:40.432 --> 15:42.017
I don't know why you play against me.

15:42.101 --> 15:44.687
- It's good aerobics.
- Yeah, for me.

15:44.770 --> 15:47.856
I'm running around like crazy.
I'm gasping for air. You just...

15:47.940 --> 15:50.776
You just stand at the net.
Somehow it's six-love, six-love.

15:50.859 --> 15:52.903
- Six-love?
- Six feet...

15:52.986 --> 15:55.572
You get perverse pleasure
beating your only son like this?

15:55.656 --> 15:56.824
Yeah, a lot.

16:00.327 --> 16:01.495
Listen, Dad...

16:02.830 --> 16:06.917
Francine wants to know if you are coming
to Lindsay's bat mitzvah.

16:08.043 --> 16:11.255
My daughter wants to know if I'm coming
to my granddaughter's bat mitzvah?

16:11.338 --> 16:13.966
- Why wouldn't I?
- She says you never RSVP'd.

16:15.509 --> 16:19.263
Why didn't she just call
instead of asking you to ask me?

16:19.346 --> 16:21.140
Dad, don't be upset.
You know how she gets.

16:21.223 --> 16:22.891
It'll be a fun day. We'll be together.

16:22.975 --> 16:25.352
I don't want Lindsay to think
that I wasn't gonna come.

16:25.436 --> 16:27.646
Who knows what your sister says to her?

16:27.730 --> 16:29.648
Just give her a call.

16:31.734 --> 16:34.903
This was fun. I'll see you next week?

16:34.987 --> 16:37.573
When I lose to you, again.

16:37.656 --> 16:39.074
I gotta go.

16:39.158 --> 16:41.869
I have a 3:00. I'm a little nervous.

16:41.952 --> 16:45.748
I'm submitting my design
for a new building in Union Square.

16:45.831 --> 16:48.334
Well, it could be a big thing for me.

16:48.417 --> 16:50.794
I RSVP'd. I know I RSVP'd.

16:50.878 --> 16:54.006
Dad, don't worry about that.
And wish me luck.

16:54.715 --> 16:55.841
About what?

16:58.093 --> 17:00.012
For my building, for the design.

17:00.679 --> 17:04.892
Oh, oh, oh, yeah, yeah, yeah. Yeah.

17:05.893 --> 17:07.561
Yeah. I'll see you.

17:09.145 --> 17:11.106
I'm gonna call her right now.

17:11.190 --> 17:13.609
<i>Daddy! Daddy!</i>

17:13.692 --> 17:14.902
Daddy!

17:14.985 --> 17:16.111
Daddy!

17:16.194 --> 17:19.280
I did something wrong, Daddy!

17:19.365 --> 17:22.116
I'm scared! Daddy!

17:23.160 --> 17:25.328
<i>Daddy!</i>

17:34.338 --> 17:37.883
Oh, hi. This is... Craziest thing. I...

17:37.966 --> 17:40.761
- I forgot what locker I was using.
- That's okay.

17:40.844 --> 17:41.804
I have a master.

17:42.888 --> 17:45.933
- Let's start with this row.
- Okay, good.

18:11.125 --> 18:12.584
That's perfect.

18:12.668 --> 18:15.879
You're gonna crush this.
Give me a high-five.

18:17.131 --> 18:19.925
I'm proud of you.
You're doing so beautifully.

18:20.009 --> 18:24.096
Yeah. I'm just getting a little nervous
about my speech.

18:24.179 --> 18:27.391
- Have you started writing it yet?
- Yeah.

18:30.936 --> 18:32.521
It's your grandfather.

18:34.356 --> 18:35.274
Hi, Papa Charlie.

18:35.357 --> 18:38.193
Hey, Lindsay, honey.
How's my bat mitzvah girl?

18:38.277 --> 18:39.528
Good.

18:39.611 --> 18:40.988
Ask him if he's coming.

18:41.071 --> 18:42.865
What do you mean? Grandpa's not coming?

18:42.948 --> 18:44.908
- Are you coming?
- That's why I'm calling.

18:46.618 --> 18:49.163
Of course I'm coming.
I wouldn't miss that for the world.

18:49.246 --> 18:52.583
- Great. I'm so happy.
- <i>Hey, when you're happy, I'm happy.</i>

18:52.666 --> 18:56.587
- Can I speak to your Mom?
- <i>Tell him I can't talk to him right now.</i>

18:58.339 --> 19:00.674
She said she'll call you back.

19:01.258 --> 19:03.052
Yeah. Okay.

19:03.135 --> 19:04.595
I can't wait to see you.

19:04.678 --> 19:05.929
<i>I can't wait to see you too.</i>

19:06.013 --> 19:08.932
So tell me. You got a pretty dress?

19:09.016 --> 19:10.726
You're gonna have to see when you come.

19:10.809 --> 19:13.020
<i>Okay.</i>

19:14.313 --> 19:16.690
Can you help me with my speech?

19:16.774 --> 19:19.735
Yeah, of course.
We'll punch it up real good.

19:20.903 --> 19:24.406
- Yeah.
- <i>Okay, kid. See you soon.</i>

19:25.157 --> 19:26.825
I had a bad day.

19:27.826 --> 19:31.121
Thanks for seeing me so late.
I really appreciate it.

19:31.205 --> 19:37.336
I... I couldn't remember
where my locker was in my health club.

19:37.419 --> 19:39.588
I've been going there for years.

19:40.214 --> 19:42.091
So damn embarrassing.

19:42.174 --> 19:44.009
That should be expected.

19:44.093 --> 19:47.888
Don't panic.
Are you doing what we talked about?

19:48.889 --> 19:51.600
Yeah. I tried not to vary my routine.

19:51.684 --> 19:55.062
I walk the same way to work every day.
I eat right.

19:55.854 --> 19:57.731
Getting some exercise.

19:57.815 --> 20:00.234
And I'm taking my meds.

20:00.317 --> 20:02.986
And by the way, that Namenda.

20:03.070 --> 20:05.989
Oh, man, it's so constipating.

20:06.073 --> 20:07.449
- It... Sorry?
- Sorry about that.

20:07.533 --> 20:11.620
I was backed up for eight days. I felt
like a python that had swallowed a deer.

20:12.955 --> 20:16.792
Charlie, you have medicines
to help you with that,

20:16.875 --> 20:18.794
and you can always give yourself an enema.

20:18.877 --> 20:23.424
I'm saving that for my birthday.
A little something special just for me.

20:24.383 --> 20:25.467
How are you sleeping?

20:26.552 --> 20:29.805
Why sleep when you can
stay up and terrorize yourself?

20:30.723 --> 20:32.683
Maybe I get four hours, maybe.

20:32.766 --> 20:34.685
And what about those flashbacks?

20:35.561 --> 20:37.855
That's the craziest thing.

20:37.938 --> 20:41.483
I can forget what I had for lunch
while I'm having lunch.

20:41.567 --> 20:44.278
But then, something flies into my head,
like, bam!

20:44.361 --> 20:47.740
It could be a moment,
a fragment, a sentence.

20:47.823 --> 20:49.450
And it's like I'm there.

20:49.533 --> 20:53.370
Like I can see it like I saw it
way back then. It doesn't...

20:53.454 --> 20:57.082
It's almost like I can smell things.
And then, black.

20:57.166 --> 21:00.544
It just goes black,
and it goes as fast as it came.

21:00.627 --> 21:02.629
It's the craziest thing.

21:05.132 --> 21:08.802
- How's the writing going?
- I think it helps.

21:08.886 --> 21:12.473
It keeps my mind active, and it helps
strengthen my denial.

21:12.556 --> 21:15.851
You know what, this show,
it's all of these young kids.

21:15.934 --> 21:19.688
I'm like the old man on the block whose
yard you don't wanna hit the ball into.

21:20.564 --> 21:23.359
But I still get stuff on the air.

21:23.442 --> 21:25.861
I still help shape the show,

21:25.944 --> 21:29.490
and when one of my jokes hits right,
and the audience laughs,

21:29.573 --> 21:30.991
there's still nothing like it.

21:31.075 --> 21:33.535
And I still love it.

21:33.619 --> 21:35.788
Good. I think you're doing well.

21:35.871 --> 21:40.584
We're keeping this at bay,
but it's so damn unpredictable.

21:40.668 --> 21:45.297
Don't let your denial
overrule your sense of reason.

21:45.381 --> 21:48.550
There's a lot we still don't know
about this kind of dementia.

21:50.552 --> 21:51.387
Okay.

21:52.805 --> 21:54.723
- See you next month.
- Okay.

21:54.807 --> 21:57.351
- Unless you need me sooner.
- Okay.

21:57.434 --> 21:59.103
Thanks, my friend.

22:00.813 --> 22:03.607
Oh, by the way, I thought
the show last week was pretty good.

22:03.691 --> 22:05.067
Was it?

22:05.150 --> 22:08.404
- Who was on?
- You know, the guy, what's-his-name?

22:08.487 --> 22:12.491
The... From the film. He's married to...

22:12.908 --> 22:14.243
The one with the hair.

22:16.161 --> 22:18.497
Would you like some of my meds?

22:51.822 --> 22:56.744
You just gonna push the lady down, huh?
You just gonna run over somebody!

22:56.827 --> 22:58.078
You son of a bitch!

22:58.162 --> 23:01.582
Come back here and try that again,
you spineless bastard!

23:02.916 --> 23:04.585
Hey, hey, hey.

23:04.668 --> 23:06.462
What happened?

23:09.381 --> 23:14.219
I was going up the right, when I got
into a head-on collision with a dumbass

23:14.303 --> 23:18.432
who was coming down on the right side,
but really that's his left side.

23:18.515 --> 23:21.226
And it's all his fault
because this isn't England!

23:21.310 --> 23:23.395
How did you know where I live?

23:23.479 --> 23:24.813
- Google.
- Google?

23:24.897 --> 23:26.523
- Here.
- What's this?

23:26.607 --> 23:29.526
The first installment
of the money I owe you.

23:31.153 --> 23:33.113
You're a pole dancer?

23:33.197 --> 23:37.660
God, no. And this coming from a man
that makes America laugh for a living.

23:37.743 --> 23:39.036
My knee!

23:39.119 --> 23:42.414
- My fucking knees!
- Listen, listen, come upstairs.

23:42.498 --> 23:46.251
I'll clean you up a little bit,
and then we can rinse out your mouth.

23:46.335 --> 23:47.795
Come on.

23:49.421 --> 23:53.634
Oh, okay, okay,

23:54.593 --> 23:55.678
Jeez.

23:56.595 --> 24:00.557
Man, this dude is doing it. This is nice.

24:01.725 --> 24:03.811
You know a lot of old white people.

24:04.603 --> 24:06.855
Oprah Winfrey?

24:08.023 --> 24:09.775
"For Carrie"?

24:10.984 --> 24:12.486
Okay, here we go.

24:12.569 --> 24:16.990
According to this wall, not only are you
ancient, but you're also famous.

24:17.074 --> 24:17.950
Sit here.

24:26.625 --> 24:28.585
You a serial killer?

24:28.669 --> 24:31.588
- What do you mean?
- Well, isn't that what serial killers do?

24:31.672 --> 24:35.300
Collect pictures of everyone they
butchered and buried in their backyard?

24:36.427 --> 24:38.053
Other knee.

24:41.265 --> 24:43.267
- Who are they?
- Who?

24:45.352 --> 24:47.354
Oh, that's my family.

24:48.188 --> 24:50.607
Why do you have
their names written down?

24:51.316 --> 24:55.070
I'm writing something about them,
and it helps me stay focused.

24:56.071 --> 24:57.406
How did you become a writer?

24:58.615 --> 25:01.410
I don't think you become one.
I think you just are.

25:02.202 --> 25:03.871
When I was a kid I thought it was fun

25:03.954 --> 25:06.123
to take the truth
and make it more interesting.

25:06.832 --> 25:07.833
So you're a liar?

25:09.043 --> 25:11.253
I'm just kidding. That's beautiful.

25:11.337 --> 25:13.422
Yeah. Well, you're as good as new.

25:14.173 --> 25:15.049
Thanks.

25:16.884 --> 25:17.926
What was here?

25:18.594 --> 25:20.596
There was some picture that fell.

25:20.679 --> 25:22.639
Housekeeper
put it someplace, I don't know.

25:23.307 --> 25:24.808
Listen, I gotta get back to work.

25:24.892 --> 25:27.895
You gotta get back to making up shit
because your real life is boring?

25:28.520 --> 25:30.064
Something like that, yeah.

25:30.564 --> 25:33.650
Thanks for bringing me the bag
of laundered money.

25:33.734 --> 25:35.652
The Corleones will be very pleased.

25:36.904 --> 25:38.364
But you didn't have to do that.

25:38.447 --> 25:41.200
That's where you're wrong,
old man. I did.

25:42.117 --> 25:42.993
Bye-bye.

25:44.953 --> 25:49.875
Next is Sarah and Roger,
Paula and Gary wrote this.

25:50.501 --> 25:52.795
A cheesy ad for a law firm.

25:53.462 --> 25:55.005
Hello, I'm Jerry Loomis.

25:55.089 --> 25:56.674
And I'm Lorraine Loomis.

25:56.757 --> 25:58.008
When we got married,

25:58.092 --> 26:01.553
the rules of dating were much
less confusing than they are today.

26:01.637 --> 26:03.055
And that's where we come in.

26:03.138 --> 26:04.348
We're the Sex Refs.

26:06.141 --> 26:08.185
We go on your dates with you.

26:08.268 --> 26:10.062
Maintaining a safe distance.

26:10.145 --> 26:11.438
So if there's any hanky...

26:11.522 --> 26:12.439
Or panky.

26:12.523 --> 26:15.734
We're there to help clarify what
both parties' intentions are.

26:15.818 --> 26:17.653
So there's no misunderstandings

26:17.736 --> 26:20.656
that could lead
to accusations and lawsuits.

26:21.240 --> 26:24.368
We deal with the he said-she said
aspects of miscommunication.

26:24.451 --> 26:28.539
For example, you're in a parked car
and she says, "Would you like to kiss me?"

26:28.622 --> 26:30.207
But he said she said:

26:30.290 --> 26:32.584
"Honey, can you please
stick your thumb up my ass?"

26:36.171 --> 26:38.298
Very different, isn't it?

26:38.799 --> 26:39.967
- We think so.
- We think so.

26:40.467 --> 26:43.053
Or if you're at the top
of the Ferris wheel,

26:43.137 --> 26:44.179
and he says:

26:44.263 --> 26:47.474
"I really don't like heights."
But she says he said:

26:47.558 --> 26:49.601
"Wanna see a picture
of my rottweiler's balls?"

26:52.563 --> 26:54.773
Now you see why you need us?

26:55.315 --> 26:58.444
We'll be there to protect you
from vicious accusations,

26:58.527 --> 27:00.863
subpoenas, and defamation suits.

27:00.946 --> 27:03.198
- "Sub-poena"?
- Yeah, remember we're on your side.

27:03.282 --> 27:04.950
No matter what side that is.

27:05.034 --> 27:06.910
- We're Loomis.
- And Loomis.

27:06.994 --> 27:08.704
And we'll see you in court...

27:08.787 --> 27:09.830
- Ship.
- Ship.

27:15.085 --> 27:16.754
That's good. That was good.

27:16.837 --> 27:17.838
It's subtle.

27:17.921 --> 27:19.340
- Yeah.
- So...

27:19.423 --> 27:23.052
Okay, good job.
Next sketch is from Darrell.

27:23.802 --> 27:26.013
Thomas Crapper Jr.

27:26.096 --> 27:29.016
We open on a 19th century
British schoolyard.

27:29.099 --> 27:31.894
A group of 9-year-old children
are milling about

27:31.977 --> 27:35.189
and trying to figure out what they want
to do now that school is let out.

27:35.272 --> 27:37.149
Wanna come over to my house?

27:37.232 --> 27:39.443
No. Your house smells.

27:39.526 --> 27:40.694
How about my house?

27:41.195 --> 27:43.989
No. Your house smells too.

27:44.073 --> 27:45.824
My house doesn't smell.

27:45.908 --> 27:46.742
How come?

27:47.451 --> 27:49.244
I'm Thomas Crapper Jr.

27:49.328 --> 27:52.122
My father invented the flush toilet.

27:52.206 --> 27:54.708
Then let's go over to his house.

27:56.585 --> 27:58.003
All right, all right.

28:00.589 --> 28:02.883
All right, guys. Very funny stuff.

28:02.966 --> 28:04.927
Let's put together a show.

28:05.594 --> 28:06.720
Sex Refs.

28:07.763 --> 28:10.265
You guys wrote a really funny sketch.

28:10.891 --> 28:12.101
But...

28:12.726 --> 28:16.146
But what? Sarah and Roger were hilarious.

28:16.230 --> 28:17.398
- Correct.
- I don't know.

28:17.481 --> 28:19.274
I don't know. Charlie, what do you think?

28:19.358 --> 28:23.570
Very funny idea. But a thumb
up the ass, rottweiler's balls...

28:23.654 --> 28:25.531
What are you talking about?
They got laughs.

28:25.614 --> 28:27.616
Of course they will. They always will.

28:27.700 --> 28:29.159
But is it the right kind of laugh?

28:29.827 --> 28:31.453
Because it's a very smart idea.

28:32.162 --> 28:33.163
Angry Librarians?

28:33.247 --> 28:34.456
- So funny.
- You should do it.

28:34.540 --> 28:35.374
I agree.

28:35.916 --> 28:37.251
Thomas Crapper Jr.

28:37.334 --> 28:38.210
Hell, no.

28:38.293 --> 28:41.005
Yeah. You know,
Darrell's option's coming up

28:41.088 --> 28:43.090
but he still hasn't gotten
a sketch on the air.

28:43.674 --> 28:44.758
It's not that bad.

28:46.301 --> 28:48.303
First of all,
if they spoke in English accents

28:48.387 --> 28:50.222
the way they were supposed to,

28:50.305 --> 28:53.475
it would've been a little bit better
but the whole thing's not framed right.

28:53.559 --> 28:55.602
Give him another shot.
He'll make it better.

28:59.064 --> 29:00.566
Listen, we hired Darrell

29:00.649 --> 29:04.278
because he wrote those
really funny essays for the <i>Lampoon.</i>

29:04.361 --> 29:06.196
I think it's a little hard
to make the leap

29:06.280 --> 29:08.282
from print to live,
that's all. It takes time.

29:08.365 --> 29:09.742
You think he's a good writer?

29:11.452 --> 29:13.495
Yeah. I think it's in there.

29:13.579 --> 29:15.205
But I think it needs to be encouraged.

29:15.289 --> 29:18.334
Listen, you guys
are a very fast crowd to run with

29:18.417 --> 29:22.338
and I also think that Inflection Mangler
Roger should be hit in the head

29:22.421 --> 29:23.922
until he says "subpoena" right.

29:24.006 --> 29:27.718
I mean, come on. "Sub-poena,"
what is that? A very small poena?

29:27.801 --> 29:29.261
That's an inferior poena.

29:29.345 --> 29:32.556
An underground poena? I mean,
what is his problem?

29:33.557 --> 29:35.392
You know, but here's the thing.

29:35.684 --> 29:37.227
There's a music to comedy.

29:37.311 --> 29:39.229
There's a music.
There are notes to comedy.

29:39.313 --> 29:41.023
- He's out of tune.
- We're working on it.

29:41.106 --> 29:43.650
Keep working because it's driving me nuts.

29:43.734 --> 29:46.820
- All right. What's next?
- I have to go.

29:46.904 --> 29:50.199
- I'm sorry, I have my... Excuse me.
- Oh, right.

29:50.282 --> 29:52.284
- Yeah.
- Have a great time.

29:52.368 --> 29:53.202
Thanks.

29:54.119 --> 29:55.037
I wish I could go.

29:55.120 --> 29:57.331
- Hey. You got a job.
- Yeah. All right.

29:57.414 --> 29:58.791
- Good night.
- Good night.

29:58.874 --> 29:59.958
Good night.

30:00.709 --> 30:03.629
They're honoring Charlie

30:03.712 --> 30:06.173
and the whole cast
at the American Film Society

30:06.256 --> 30:08.592
for the 30th anniversary
of <i>Call Me Anytime.</i>

30:09.301 --> 30:12.388
Kevin Kline, Sharon Stone,
Barry Levinson directing.

30:12.471 --> 30:15.099
Such a funny movie. Have you seen it?

30:15.808 --> 30:16.767
Yeah. It's great.

30:18.102 --> 30:20.270
All right. What's up?

30:22.147 --> 30:23.941
Look, you know I love Charlie.

30:24.608 --> 30:26.652
I know he gave you
your start and everything.

30:26.735 --> 30:28.529
But... come on.

30:29.029 --> 30:32.157
I just don't know what he brings
to the show anymore.

30:32.241 --> 30:34.243
Aside from 40 years' experience?

30:34.994 --> 30:37.246
And a body of work that includes shows

30:37.329 --> 30:39.289
that made it possible
for this show to exist?

30:41.750 --> 30:46.588
Look, I know how you
can question Charlie's value.

30:47.297 --> 30:50.426
But he's really smart
and he still writes funny jokes.

30:51.176 --> 30:52.678
And he's my consigliere.

30:53.512 --> 30:56.807
When you write sketches with
a thumb up someone's ass,

30:57.474 --> 30:59.018
or a rottweiler's balls,

30:59.727 --> 31:02.479
he's the one who reminds me
what we should be putting on the air.

31:03.689 --> 31:07.317
Bottom-line, as long as
I am producing this show,

31:07.401 --> 31:08.861
Charlie will be here.

31:10.779 --> 31:13.073
- Okay?
- You got it.

31:13.157 --> 31:14.366
- All right.
- Yeah.

31:15.200 --> 31:16.994
- Let's get back to work.
- Yeah.

31:26.628 --> 31:27.963
Go, go.

31:30.007 --> 31:31.383
Close the door, close the door.

31:33.886 --> 31:34.845
Turn off the lights.

31:36.013 --> 31:37.139
Come here.

31:40.017 --> 31:42.686
I can't do this anymore.

31:42.770 --> 31:43.687
Why?

31:44.521 --> 31:47.441
You're married, I'm married.
I don't want anyone to get hurt.

31:47.524 --> 31:48.901
Well, neither do I.

31:50.277 --> 31:52.946
I just don't know what to do.

31:53.030 --> 31:55.741
But wait, wait, wait. Let's make a plan.

31:55.824 --> 31:59.828
Every year, we will meet
here in the Tuckmans' bathroom,

31:59.912 --> 32:01.413
at their Halloween party.

32:02.289 --> 32:05.668
- What about the Tuckmans' Christmas party?
- No, we've got to be strong.

32:10.005 --> 32:12.841
Hi, how are you?
Thank you all for being here.

32:12.925 --> 32:14.885
Good evening, I'm Bob Costas.

32:16.345 --> 32:19.973
Please welcome,
the director of <i>Call Me Anytime,</i>

32:20.057 --> 32:21.225
Barry Levinson.

32:21.308 --> 32:23.560
Its writer, Charlie Burnz,

32:23.644 --> 32:27.898
and its stars,
Kevin Kline and Sharon Stone.

32:34.863 --> 32:37.074
I have to say, right off the top.

32:37.157 --> 32:39.368
I really loved this film.

32:39.451 --> 32:42.037
In fact, I'm bypassing
a Mets-Astros game tonight

32:42.121 --> 32:44.331
just to be here, to do this instead.

32:44.415 --> 32:46.333
All right, so what's the
germ of all this?

32:46.417 --> 32:47.626
How did it all get started?

32:48.502 --> 32:53.841
Well, Charlie and I originally met
on <i>The Carol Burnett Show</i> ages ago.

32:53.924 --> 32:57.177
And he wrote a lot of very funny sketches.

32:57.803 --> 33:02.099
Shy guy, always called me Mr. Levinson.

33:02.182 --> 33:03.642
Even though we were friendly.

33:04.143 --> 33:09.064
All right, what happened was I read
Charlie's script and I thought:

33:09.148 --> 33:10.691
"Well this is a perfect film to do."

33:11.483 --> 33:14.737
So the next day, I get a call
from Barry and he says:

33:14.820 --> 33:17.906
"I just read this script, it's terrific.
You gotta read it.

33:17.990 --> 33:19.700
The character, she's you."

33:19.783 --> 33:23.412
And I said, "She's completely compulsive,
she'll do anything. I'm in."

33:25.247 --> 33:31.170
And then the next day, he called me.
I read the script and then I was in.

33:31.253 --> 33:36.300
Literally three days later, we got a go.
And I called Charlie with the good news.

33:36.383 --> 33:39.553
And so Charlie, you get the call,
what did Barry say?

33:40.137 --> 33:41.138
Who?

33:41.889 --> 33:42.931
Mr. Levinson.

33:44.808 --> 33:48.645
It's so nice to see you.
Nice to... Wow.

33:48.729 --> 33:50.147
It's great to meet you.

33:50.230 --> 33:54.276
I was just thrilled and shocked that...

33:54.360 --> 33:55.569
Mr. Levinson.

33:59.990 --> 34:03.035
Wanted to direct my first...
This was my first screenplay.

34:03.118 --> 34:08.165
And that Kevin Kline was gonna play Ben,
and that... help me.

34:08.247 --> 34:10.209
- Meryl Streep.
- Hello.

34:11.126 --> 34:13.504
Was gonna play Iris.

34:13.587 --> 34:16.631
And I kept thinking,
if my parents were alive,

34:16.714 --> 34:18.425
this good news would've killed them.

34:20.218 --> 34:24.973
Charlie's work is... It's not just comedic,
there's a humanity to it.

34:25.057 --> 34:28.477
And I think it shows
people as real people.

34:28.560 --> 34:30.187
It's exceptional writing.

34:38.278 --> 34:41.448
Hey, old man. You were great up there.

34:41.531 --> 34:44.118
Hey. You were inside?

34:44.201 --> 34:47.413
Yeah. And I loved it. Second installment.

34:47.495 --> 34:50.749
It's a little light, boss.
Please don't break my thumbs.

34:51.917 --> 34:54.878
Well, this is a lovely surprise.

34:54.962 --> 34:56.504
How'd you know about this?

34:56.588 --> 34:57.673
My loser ex.

34:57.756 --> 35:00.718
I used his ticket.
You made me laugh a lot.

35:00.801 --> 35:01.969
I'm really sorry.

35:03.762 --> 35:06.724
No, I like seeing you up there.
It was so cool.

35:06.807 --> 35:08.642
You've done a lot of big things.

35:08.726 --> 35:09.810
I got lucky.

35:09.893 --> 35:12.521
Being good
ain't got nothing to do with luck.

35:13.272 --> 35:14.231
I guess.

35:16.233 --> 35:17.818
Why do you have birds in your hair?

35:17.901 --> 35:18.861
Why not?

35:19.403 --> 35:20.863
Shit, what time is it?

35:21.447 --> 35:23.115
I'm gonna be late for work.

35:23.198 --> 35:24.616
- I gotta go. Come with me.
- Work?

35:24.700 --> 35:25.784
- Yeah. Come on.
- Now?

35:25.868 --> 35:26.702
Yeah.

35:26.785 --> 35:28.120
What do you do?

