<i>I'm mad at ya
'Cause your feet's too big</i>

36:17.378 --> 36:19.880
<i>I hate ya
'Cause your feet's too big</i>

36:21.340 --> 36:24.218
Yeah, I come from a pretty small family.

36:25.552 --> 36:28.847
My mom and dad were singers.

36:28.931 --> 36:30.265
Mo and Jessie.

36:30.808 --> 36:32.726
They were kind of like
Ashford and Simpson.

36:32.810 --> 36:34.186
But they never made it big

36:34.269 --> 36:37.648
because there was already
an Ashford and Simpson.

36:38.273 --> 36:41.068
We used to have a lot of fun,
they thought me how to harmonize,

36:41.568 --> 36:45.781
and my dad made these
really cool weathervanes.

36:45.864 --> 36:50.119
And my mom, she had these
beautiful dreamcatchers that she makes.

36:50.202 --> 36:53.539
They live just outside of Charlotte.
I love them both to pieces.

36:54.081 --> 36:55.165
They sound great.

36:58.711 --> 37:01.046
I love the way
the air smells after it rains.

37:02.339 --> 37:06.218
Listen, if you ever need my help
with what you're going through right now,

37:06.885 --> 37:09.638
even if you need someone to talk to,
I'm here.

37:09.722 --> 37:13.100
Well, thank you very much.
But what are you talking about?

37:13.809 --> 37:16.186
You forgot Sharon Stone
and Barry Levinson's names?

37:16.854 --> 37:18.522
Oh, that. I get a little tongue tied.

37:18.605 --> 37:19.940
I don't like being on-stage.

37:20.024 --> 37:21.150
And what stage were you on

37:21.233 --> 37:23.652
when you wrote your family's names
under their pictures?

37:23.736 --> 37:25.029
I told you, that's how I work.

37:25.112 --> 37:27.239
It's a project that I'm working on, and...

37:27.322 --> 37:30.617
Look, I know what you told me,
but don't bullshit me, old man.

37:34.747 --> 37:36.498
It started innocently enough.

37:37.249 --> 37:41.337
I'd have trouble remembering things.
A name, a place, a fork.

37:42.254 --> 37:44.214
And I think,
"You're getting older, Charlie.

37:44.298 --> 37:46.050
You know, you're having senior moments."

37:46.925 --> 37:48.969
But one day,
I'm having lunch with this guy,

37:49.053 --> 37:50.846
and I can't remember his name.

37:50.929 --> 37:52.890
He's going on and on and on.

37:52.973 --> 37:54.350
I'm thinking, "Who the hell is this?"

37:54.433 --> 37:56.769
Then he cracks himself up
and he starts laughing.

37:56.852 --> 37:59.646
So I faked laughing.
Just to go along with him.

37:59.730 --> 38:05.069
And while I'm laughing, I'm panicking.
Thinking, "Who the hell is this?"

38:05.152 --> 38:06.570
Did you know him?

38:08.405 --> 38:09.698
He was my son.

38:13.702 --> 38:16.580
Yeah. It's happening.

38:18.290 --> 38:21.001
Jesus, old man. I'm sorry.

38:26.924 --> 38:27.800
Who's Carrie?

38:29.677 --> 38:32.721
I saw that on the title page
at your house.

38:34.723 --> 38:36.141
Carrie was my wife.

38:37.601 --> 38:38.519
She died.

38:40.437 --> 38:41.772
Long time ago.

38:43.941 --> 38:47.319
And I'm writing something for her.

38:48.070 --> 38:50.406
And I have to finish
before my words run out.

38:50.489 --> 38:52.324
When did you start working on it?

38:53.075 --> 38:55.077
About an hour after I was diagnosed.

38:56.078 --> 38:57.329
And how's it going?

38:57.413 --> 38:58.872
It's going really well.

38:59.665 --> 39:02.793
My mama would call that
a crock of lukewarm horseshit.

39:02.876 --> 39:04.461
Don't lie to me, old man.

39:05.045 --> 39:07.589
I know you haven't started
writing one single word.

39:08.674 --> 39:10.342
- Let me see your phone.
- My phone?

39:10.426 --> 39:11.635
- Your phone.
- Okay.

39:13.220 --> 39:14.096
Okay.

39:15.055 --> 39:18.767
This is my name, this is my number, okay?

39:18.851 --> 39:20.602
Now, even if you don't wanna contact me,

39:20.686 --> 39:25.649
I just want you to know that I'm not some
allergic-to-shellfish nut

39:25.733 --> 39:27.484
that's half your age plus four,

39:27.568 --> 39:29.695
that wants to help you
because you helped me.

39:30.320 --> 39:31.905
You don't stop for commas, do you?

39:32.614 --> 39:33.991
Life's too short for commas.

39:41.081 --> 39:43.876
Darrell, this is better.

39:44.543 --> 39:45.919
Try this as a tag.

39:47.087 --> 39:50.215
Let's do it in the dress rehearsal.
What do you think?

39:51.175 --> 39:53.344
Yeah. That's great.

39:53.427 --> 39:54.970
- Are we good?
- Yeah. Thanks.

39:55.054 --> 39:56.347
- Good. Alrighty.
- All right.

39:57.848 --> 39:59.600
Do you want to come to my house and play?

39:59.683 --> 40:01.852
No, your house smells.

40:02.603 --> 40:04.521
Then come to my house and play.

40:04.605 --> 40:07.399
No, your house smells too.

40:08.442 --> 40:11.528
My house doesn't smell. We can play there.

40:11.612 --> 40:13.530
Oh, he's Thomas Crapper's son.

40:13.614 --> 40:15.449
His father invented the flushing toilet.

40:16.200 --> 40:17.910
That's a lot of crap.

40:18.619 --> 40:20.871
Not anymore.

40:20.954 --> 40:22.998
Let's go to his house!

40:23.749 --> 40:29.046
Ah, yes. Thomas Crapper,
the father of the modern toilet.

40:29.129 --> 40:31.173
I'm Jeff Goldblum.

40:34.968 --> 40:41.016
This has been a little-known moment
in indoor plumbing history.

40:42.643 --> 40:46.063
Change your toilet. Change the world.

40:47.022 --> 40:48.941
Commercial break! Two minutes.

40:52.152 --> 40:53.153
Not bad.

40:53.237 --> 40:56.115
- Great fix, Darrell.
- The Goldblum thing was funny.

40:56.198 --> 40:57.074
Thanks.

40:57.157 --> 41:01.370
I think we'll slot it after the third
commercial break. Got one on the air.

41:01.453 --> 41:02.621
All right.

41:04.164 --> 41:06.375
Yeah. Yeah.

41:30.858 --> 41:32.317
<i>How did you meet Carrie?</i>

41:42.077 --> 41:44.997
<i>Come on, old man. How did you two meet?</i>

41:53.297 --> 41:55.215
Damn it, I hate this stuff.

41:56.967 --> 41:58.802
Hey, you know what really does the trick?

42:00.137 --> 42:01.138
What?

42:01.221 --> 42:02.097
Butter.

42:03.098 --> 42:05.267
- Did you just say butter?
- I'm telling you. Butter.

42:05.351 --> 42:08.270
No, really. There's a lot of tar
on the beach this year.

42:08.354 --> 42:12.399
What you do is you take a stick of butter
and just keep rubbing it into the tar

42:12.483 --> 42:15.903
and somehow it breaks it down,
you can just wipe it away

42:15.986 --> 42:18.113
and you don't have to use
that tomahawk of a shell

42:18.197 --> 42:20.115
that you're using
which is probably taking off

42:20.199 --> 42:22.076
all the epidermis
on the bottom of your foot.

42:22.785 --> 42:24.787
- Hi.
- Hi.

42:24.870 --> 42:26.205
I'm Charlie Burnz.

42:26.288 --> 42:27.539
Hello, Charlie Burnz.

42:29.750 --> 42:30.876
I'm Carrie.

42:30.959 --> 42:35.089
Carrie? Is that short for Caren
or Carina or a Catherine?

42:35.589 --> 42:37.716
- Florence.
- Florence?

42:37.800 --> 42:38.717
Don't ask.

42:39.218 --> 42:41.804
Florence. Well that's a great
old-fashioned name.

42:41.887 --> 42:44.014
That's one of the names
of one of my relatives.

42:44.098 --> 42:46.975
I could never imagine
my relatives as babies.

42:47.059 --> 42:48.477
Herman, come away from the water.

42:48.560 --> 42:50.688
Irving, don't put that
puppy in your mouth.

42:50.771 --> 42:54.358
Mildred just pooped in the toilet.
A big hand for Mildred.

42:54.942 --> 42:57.611
- You don't hear those names.
- That's true.

42:59.154 --> 43:02.908
Listen, I live in that white house,
like, right over there.

43:02.991 --> 43:05.911
And I happen to have
like half a ton of butter.

43:05.995 --> 43:07.037
So, if you...

43:07.121 --> 43:11.500
Yeah, I won a dairy contest.
You had to guess how much the cow weighed.

43:11.583 --> 43:13.961
And I can de-tar you.

43:14.044 --> 43:16.338
And I mean that in a very respectful way.

43:18.424 --> 43:19.508
Okay.

43:27.391 --> 43:29.059
Wow, is that a paint-by-number?

43:29.977 --> 43:33.355
It's you again. Hello, Charlie Burnz.

43:33.439 --> 43:34.523
Hey, Carrie.

43:35.190 --> 43:36.233
It's really good.

43:36.316 --> 43:37.860
- Yeah? You like it?
- Yeah.

43:37.943 --> 43:39.528
- You know what else I like?
- What?

43:39.611 --> 43:41.822
- Steamed clams.
- Oh, yeah?

43:41.905 --> 43:44.324
- Yeah.
- I've never had steamed clams.

43:44.408 --> 43:46.535
Okay, my house, 7 p.m.

43:47.995 --> 43:48.829
Deal.

43:50.039 --> 43:55.586
Here we go. Okay, take the clam.
Spread it apart. Rinse it in the broth.

43:56.170 --> 43:59.256
And then to the butter.
And then to your mouth.

43:59.340 --> 44:01.633
It's a little bit of heaven.
Isn't it great?

44:02.384 --> 44:04.219
Oh, God. Oh, my God. I'm so sorry.

44:04.303 --> 44:05.971
That's disgusting.

44:06.055 --> 44:08.223
- Please don't sue.
- Oh, man.

44:09.516 --> 44:11.352
- Pizza?
- I'll call Gino's.

44:24.948 --> 44:26.784
I just got this rug.

44:27.910 --> 44:29.662
This is like tracking Bigfoot.

44:35.584 --> 44:36.460
Hey.

44:37.419 --> 44:38.420
Hey.

44:38.504 --> 44:39.672
Carrie.

44:40.673 --> 44:41.757
Good morning.

44:46.679 --> 44:47.554
Here.

44:49.264 --> 44:51.558
Good morning, Charlie Burnz.

44:53.310 --> 44:56.313
Here. A little something for breakfast.

44:56.939 --> 44:58.357
It's a beautiful day.

45:03.237 --> 45:04.655
Oh, God.

45:08.325 --> 45:09.493
Okay.

45:11.453 --> 45:12.788
De-tar me.

45:13.372 --> 45:16.208
But it seems a shame to waste
the butter on my foot.

45:17.292 --> 45:18.627
Come here.

45:18.711 --> 45:19.837
Okay.

45:22.506 --> 45:23.382
Hi.

45:39.565 --> 45:41.775
Well, hello. Old friend.

46:33.577 --> 46:38.999
<i>And you can't tell the depth of a well
By the length of the handle on the pump</i>

46:39.083 --> 46:42.544
<i>Baby, how can you tell about me?</i>

46:43.921 --> 46:46.423
<i>Now you can't tell a bottle by the label</i>

46:46.507 --> 46:48.884
<i>That's how it is with me</i>

46:48.967 --> 46:51.804
<i>Some folks call me a ladle,</i>

46:51.887 --> 46:55.724
<i>Give me a chance and you'll see</i>

46:55.808 --> 46:59.978
<i>You can't tell the depth of a well
By the length of the handle on the pump</i>

47:00.062 --> 47:00.896
Thank you, boo.

47:00.979 --> 47:04.650
<i>Baby, baby, baby</i>

47:04.733 --> 47:08.487
<i>Baby, baby
Baby, baby, baby</i>

47:08.570 --> 47:12.366
<i>How can you tell about me? Yeah</i>

47:12.449 --> 47:15.327
All right now,
make sure you make a donation.

47:16.286 --> 47:18.080
Thank you,
we'll see you in a few months.

47:18.163 --> 47:19.456
We're going on tour.

47:19.540 --> 47:23.544
A tour. Four months, 50 cities.
Theaters, clubs.

47:23.627 --> 47:25.504
- And we got a tour bus.
- Can you believe it?

47:25.587 --> 47:27.840
Man, it's awesome. I'm in, all the way.

47:27.923 --> 47:29.883
- Awesome.
- All right guys, I'll see you later.

47:29.967 --> 47:31.510
- See you.
- That's cool.

47:33.012 --> 47:34.096
You sounded great.

47:35.806 --> 47:36.932
What are you doing here?

47:37.016 --> 47:40.811
Em, I'm sorry. I messed up. Please.

47:40.894 --> 47:44.732
It's too late. I've moved on,
I met someone and we're in love.

47:44.815 --> 47:47.693
What? Already? Bullshit.

47:47.776 --> 47:49.695
- He's over there. Wanna meet him?
- Okay.

47:49.778 --> 47:51.864
Come on,
you'll see if it's some bullshit or not.

47:53.032 --> 47:54.658
- Hey.
- Hey, old man.

47:54.742 --> 47:57.745
Hi. Hey, you were great.
I mean, that was just terrific.

47:58.245 --> 47:59.246
What is going on here?

48:00.039 --> 48:04.168
Charlie, this is my ex-boyfriend,
Dwayne St. John.

48:04.793 --> 48:07.421
- Oh, I hear you're a fan. Thank you.
- This is your boyfriend?

48:07.504 --> 48:10.382
- No, he's my bae.
- You used my auction thing!

48:10.466 --> 48:12.551
Oh, yeah, all $22 of it.

48:12.634 --> 48:15.471
And thank you. It's the first day
of the rest of my life.

48:15.554 --> 48:16.388
Ain't that right?

48:17.222 --> 48:18.307
Yeah.

48:18.932 --> 48:22.311
- I love everything you do.
- And now he's doing me.

48:22.394 --> 48:24.146
Ain't that right, Charlie?

48:24.229 --> 48:26.190
You got that right... baby.

48:27.441 --> 48:28.817
We are late for lunch.

48:28.901 --> 48:32.571
And I would love
a seafood salad right now.

48:33.489 --> 48:35.824
- Okay.
- This is so crazy.

48:36.825 --> 48:39.244
In acting class,
I was doing the scene from your play...

48:39.328 --> 48:40.829
Do you wanna just take a picture?

48:41.497 --> 48:43.999
- Could I? Okay with you, sir?
- Sure.

48:44.083 --> 48:47.044
- Man, this is amazing.
- I'll take it. I know the password.

48:47.586 --> 48:49.129
All right, get closer.

48:50.047 --> 48:51.340
Okay, now, smile.

48:51.423 --> 48:54.134
Put your hands up in the air.
Yeah, like you won something.

48:56.261 --> 48:58.013
There you go. Okay.
Charlie, come up here.

48:58.097 --> 48:59.765
Is this good enough?

49:02.351 --> 49:06.480
Now you'll always remember
what me and your idol look like together.

49:06.563 --> 49:07.648
Bye-bye.

49:13.737 --> 49:15.864
- You okay?
- I will be.

49:16.699 --> 49:19.451
- I want some ice cream.
- Okay.

49:19.535 --> 49:22.079
And a triple vegan delight.

49:22.162 --> 49:24.415
Wow, that looks like the Olympic torch.

49:25.249 --> 49:26.959
Hey, I gotta change the name.

49:30.879 --> 49:32.506
So when would you leave?

49:33.173 --> 49:36.301
In like a month or so.
It's crazy how things happened.

49:36.385 --> 49:40.180
This record producer saw our videos and...

49:40.848 --> 49:43.517
he was digging us,
next thing you know, bam!

49:43.600 --> 49:47.146
We going on tour for four months,
on a tour bus,

49:47.229 --> 49:50.357
and we're already
talking about doing an album, it's...

49:50.441 --> 49:53.986
Charlie, I'm sorry. I'm doing all the
talking. You said something good happened?

49:54.862 --> 49:57.865
- I wrote last night.
- You did? That's awesome.

49:57.948 --> 49:59.783
It was fantastic. Just like the old days.

49:59.867 --> 50:02.703
Itzhak Perlman starting playing,
and I started writing.

50:03.329 --> 50:05.122
Izzy Perlman? Who's Izzy Perlman?

50:05.205 --> 50:06.623
Not Izzy Perlman.

50:06.707 --> 50:09.626
Izzy Pearlman
sold my parents' Venetian blinds.

50:09.710 --> 50:13.505
Itzhak Perlman is one
of the greatest violinists in the world.

50:13.589 --> 50:14.965
Ask your phone who he is!

50:15.049 --> 50:18.385
He lives in the building behind me
and he likes to practice at night.

50:18.469 --> 50:21.930
I just open my window
and it's like a free Itzhak festival.

50:22.014 --> 50:24.099
One of the reasons
Carrie and I bought the place.

50:30.773 --> 50:32.274
What was that for?

50:32.358 --> 50:35.277
Don't think I would've written anything
if you didn't get me started.

50:37.237 --> 50:39.114
- You're welcome.
- Thank you.

50:42.493 --> 50:43.410
Hey...

50:44.203 --> 50:46.497
- Are you doing anything right now?
- No.

50:47.247 --> 50:49.917
It's my day off. Wanna have some laughs?

50:50.000 --> 50:52.419
- Hell, yeah.
- Come on.

50:53.170 --> 50:55.964
- Wax museum?
- Trust me, it's fun.

50:56.048 --> 50:57.633
Don't tell me there's one of you.

50:57.716 --> 50:59.259
- Come on.
- Okay.

51:01.053 --> 51:03.639
This is Marilyn Monroe
from <i>The Seven Year Itch.</i>

51:04.306 --> 51:07.851
I'd be itchy too if I had
hot subway air blowing up my ass.

51:07.935 --> 51:09.687
Is that who I think it is?

51:10.979 --> 51:13.232
Hello, Dalai.

51:13.315 --> 51:15.651
Come on, queen. Smile, girl. Smile.

51:17.403 --> 51:19.488
What could he possibly be thinking?

51:21.073 --> 51:23.450
"Shouldn't have had the seafood salad."

51:24.660 --> 51:26.245
- Picasso.
- I don't dig him.

51:26.328 --> 51:27.204
- Why?
- Sexist.

51:27.287 --> 51:30.040
If I did a painting of you
with three willies, would you be happy?

51:30.124 --> 51:31.291
I'd be ecstatic.

51:32.668 --> 51:36.797
The Theory of Relativity
is never lend your relatives money.

51:36.880 --> 51:39.091
You can kiss that ten bucks goodbye.

51:42.052 --> 51:43.804
Golda, tell me again.
I don't understand.

51:43.887 --> 51:45.180
Okay, Mr. Arafat.

51:45.264 --> 51:47.725
It's "Chanukah," not "Hanukkah."

51:47.808 --> 51:49.351
I'm having trouble with the...

51:49.435 --> 51:51.353
I'm having trouble with the...!

51:51.979 --> 51:53.897
Pope? Party of five?

51:54.648 --> 51:57.735
- I am not a crook.
- Oh, bullshit, Dickie.

51:57.818 --> 51:59.486
Then why are you so sweaty?

52:00.029 --> 52:01.905
Man, he is really cross-eyed.

52:01.989 --> 52:05.034
That's why he didn't find
any weapons of mass destruction.

52:08.579 --> 52:10.289
- So you have two kids, right?
- Yeah.

52:10.372 --> 52:14.043
Francine teaches math
at a middle school in New Jersey.

52:14.126 --> 52:16.170
And my son Rex is an architect.

52:16.253 --> 52:18.213
And Rex is a...

52:19.048 --> 52:20.758
He's a pretty brilliant kid.

52:20.841 --> 52:24.136
He should be. He was born
at the American Museum of Natural History.

52:25.846 --> 52:28.140
This was so nice. Thank you.

52:31.268 --> 52:35.105
I wanna ask you a question.
And I'm a little nervous about it,

52:35.189 --> 52:38.275
because I don't remember
the last time I asked this, if ever.

52:40.819 --> 52:44.114
Would like to be my date
for my granddaughter's bat mitzvah?

52:44.198 --> 52:47.034
Her name's Lindsay
and she's the love of my life.

52:47.117 --> 52:48.994
And it would be
like a goodbye party for you

52:49.078 --> 52:51.205
except it's a bat mitzvah and not for you.

52:51.288 --> 52:53.707
I've never been to one before. When is it?

52:54.875 --> 52:57.628
- I don't remember, but soon.
- Way to narrow it down.

52:57.711 --> 53:01.090
- I have the invitation...
- Doesn't matter when.

53:01.173 --> 53:02.841
- I'd be happy to go.
- Yeah?

53:02.925 --> 53:04.927
- But only on one condition.
- What?

53:05.636 --> 53:06.804
That we dance together.

53:06.887 --> 53:09.598
Oh, no, no, no. You don't understand.
I'm a dangerous dancer.

53:09.682 --> 53:11.642
One of the few with mambo insurance.

53:11.725 --> 53:14.561
Oh, come on, Charlie.
It'll be so much fun.

53:15.187 --> 53:19.191
All right. But to be on the safe side,
wear a helmet and shoulder pads.

53:19.274 --> 53:21.318
- Done.
- Great.

53:49.471 --> 53:51.056
What's the matter, Carrie?

53:51.140 --> 53:53.434
I don't want the summer to be over.

53:53.517 --> 53:54.601
Well...

53:55.477 --> 53:58.230
maybe we just keep
our summer going forever.

54:00.482 --> 54:02.067
Good idea, Charlie Burnz.

54:24.089 --> 54:26.550
Stop sign... Left.

54:27.551 --> 54:29.928
Whoa, sorry, pal.
You can't go this way. Not safe.

54:30.012 --> 54:33.057
- This is the way I go.
- Sir, go this way. Not safe here.

54:33.140 --> 54:35.934
- I don't know that way.
- You gotta go that way.

54:36.018 --> 54:38.854
I don't know that way,
this is the way I go every day.

54:38.937 --> 54:41.315
It's a new day.
Cross the street and you'll be fine.

54:41.398 --> 54:44.318
- No! I have to go this way!
- Come on. Move!

54:48.072 --> 54:49.281
Sorry.

54:49.365 --> 54:51.116
What's the matter with you?

54:54.995 --> 54:58.749
That's the way I go. I go that way.

55:03.170 --> 55:06.423
What, are you crazy?
What are you doing?

55:07.049 --> 55:08.842
Get the hell out of the way!

55:10.177 --> 55:11.053
Hey!

55:11.887 --> 55:13.263
You, old man!

55:14.306 --> 55:17.935
Get the hell out of the way!
You're in the middle of the road!

55:18.727 --> 55:19.937
What, are you deaf?

56:00.227 --> 56:04.606
<i>Hey, old man! Am I crazy or did you say
your son was born in a museum?</i>

56:07.151 --> 56:09.737
Look at the size of this thing, honey.

56:09.820 --> 56:11.613
- Charlie...
- This is the only thing here

56:11.697 --> 56:14.408
that's bigger than you.
Look at that wishbone!

56:14.491 --> 56:15.784
- Charlie.
- What?

56:16.577 --> 56:18.245
I think my water just broke.

56:19.121 --> 56:22.708
We gotta get you out of here.
We gotta get you out of here.

56:25.085 --> 56:27.629
- I'm not gonna make it.
- Honey... I need a doctor!

56:27.713 --> 56:29.757
- I need a doctor!
- What's the problem?

56:29.840 --> 56:31.258
- My wife's having a baby.
- When?

56:31.342 --> 56:32.885
- Now!
- I'm gonna ask the supervisor

56:32.968 --> 56:34.887
- if that's okay.
- Are you kidding me?!

56:34.970 --> 56:36.597
- I am a doctor.
- What kind?

56:36.680 --> 56:38.515
- Proctologist. Okay.
- Close enough.

56:38.599 --> 56:40.601
Oh, God. This baby's coming fast.

56:40.684 --> 56:43.187
Can you do it somewhere else?
A tour group's coming through.

56:43.270 --> 56:45.230
Really?! I have a baby coming through!

56:45.314 --> 56:47.524
Take a deep breath. Relax.
Call an ambulance now.

56:47.608 --> 56:49.485
- Copy that.
- Hi.

56:49.568 --> 56:52.071
- You should know my name. It's Carrie.
- Hi. Hello.

56:52.154 --> 56:54.698
And that man
who looks so scared is Charlie.

56:54.782 --> 56:57.409
- Hi, Charlie.
- He's the daddy.

56:57.493 --> 56:58.661
- Good.
- What's your name?

56:58.744 --> 57:02.581
I'm Joe Katz. Okay? Take a breath.
Relax. You're doing just great.

57:02.665 --> 57:05.459
Now, listen.
I'll have to remove your underwear.

57:05.542 --> 57:08.796
Oh, that's a bit aggressive
for our first date, don't you think?

57:08.879 --> 57:09.963
There we go.

57:11.048 --> 57:12.800
- What should I do next?
- Nothing!

57:12.883 --> 57:14.718
Sure? They gave us a class with the doll...

57:14.802 --> 57:16.387
- Leave us alone!
- Okay. Sorry.

57:16.470 --> 57:19.890
Charlie. This is like that time
at Rye Playland, remember?

57:19.973 --> 57:22.976
At the top of the Ferris wheel?
We were so drunk!

57:23.811 --> 57:25.479
- You okay?
- Just trying to think.

57:25.562 --> 57:27.981
Who took your panties off
at Rye Playland? I wasn't there.

57:28.065 --> 57:29.817
- What?
- It was Coney Island!

57:29.900 --> 57:31.860
Oh, you're right!

57:31.944 --> 57:34.154
- Oh, God.
- Lean forward slowly.

57:34.238 --> 57:36.657
And you're gonna push when I tell you.

57:36.740 --> 57:39.326
Carrie, you're doing great.
Hey! What are you looking at?

57:40.119 --> 57:42.663
- And get these scouts out of here!
- Come on, guys. Let's go.

57:42.746 --> 57:44.832
- Come on, boys.
- This is bullshit!

57:45.624 --> 57:47.668
- You too!
- Copy that. And just a reminder:

57:47.751 --> 57:49.712
- we close at 5.
- Get out of here!

57:50.337 --> 57:52.464
Okay. The baby's here. The baby's here.

57:52.548 --> 57:55.217
Pull a big deep breath
and a big push, okay?

57:55.300 --> 57:57.428
- You can do it. There you go.
- Okay.

58:05.811 --> 58:08.647
Okay. Here you go. Here you go.

58:08.731 --> 58:09.773
Here you go.

58:10.607 --> 58:14.069
It's a boy. It's a boy. It's a boy.

58:16.739 --> 58:17.823
<i>Hey, Charlie.</i>

58:17.906 --> 58:18.991
Yeah?

58:20.367 --> 58:21.869
Let's name him Rex.

58:24.705 --> 58:26.540
That's the perfect name.

58:28.584 --> 58:31.420
I'm really glad we didn't have him
under that big whale.

58:31.503 --> 58:36.675
Yeah. Because Moby Dick Burnz
would be a terrible name for our son.

58:36.759 --> 58:38.886
He'd have so much trouble at school.

58:40.471 --> 58:43.140
Oh, I love you, Charlie Burnz.

58:45.642 --> 58:46.935
I love you too.

59:19.760 --> 59:23.764
All right, Roger.
We'll cue you in five, four...

59:23.847 --> 59:26.517
Three, two, one...

59:27.059 --> 59:28.894
Good evening.
And welcome to another episode

59:28.977 --> 59:31.355
of <i>Old People Who Have
Always Looked Old!</i>

59:31.438 --> 59:34.817
Tonight's subjects are Keith Richards
and the late Mother Teresa.

59:34.900 --> 59:37.069
- Oh, boy. Did you hear it?
- Yeah.

59:37.152 --> 59:39.154
- How does he get away with this?
- I don't know.

59:39.905 --> 59:41.073
All right, listen.

59:42.074 --> 59:44.868
The sketch ideas are good,
but they don't always have to be so big.

59:44.952 --> 59:47.705
Sketches can be small, more personal.

59:47.788 --> 59:50.833
Something about yourself,
maybe about your girlfriend or something.

59:50.916 --> 59:53.002
- That would be a problem.
- Why's that?

59:53.085 --> 59:55.963
I don't have one. I'm incredibly single.

59:56.046 --> 59:57.464
See? That's funny.

59:57.548 --> 59:59.967
That I eat every meal alone?

1:00:00.050 --> 1:00:02.469
- Oh, that's hilarious.
- No, no.

1:00:02.553 --> 1:00:04.722
I'm talking
about a character for the show.

1:00:04.805 --> 1:00:07.975
The incredibly single guy.
It's different than being single.

1:00:08.058 --> 1:00:11.020
It's incredibly single.
There might be something funny in that.

1:00:11.103 --> 1:00:12.938
- Right.
- Find out what's funny about you

1:00:13.022 --> 1:00:16.233
- and then write about it.
- Okay. I'll try that.

1:00:16.316 --> 1:00:19.069
- Okay.
- Can I tell you something?

1:00:19.153 --> 1:00:20.029
Yeah.

1:00:20.696 --> 1:00:23.115
When I was at Harvard,
I had a humor class

1:00:23.198 --> 1:00:25.117
and I wrote a paper as you.

1:00:26.076 --> 1:00:27.369
- Really?
- Yeah.

1:00:27.453 --> 1:00:30.831
I read all your plays,
I knew your movie scripts.

1:00:30.914 --> 1:00:34.668
I could even tell what jokes were yours
on whatever TV show you were writing on.

1:00:34.752 --> 1:00:38.047
So I wrote a paper in your style.
Like you were at Harvard.

1:00:39.173 --> 1:00:40.215
And how'd it do?

1:00:41.133 --> 1:00:41.967
Got an F.

1:00:43.052 --> 1:00:46.013
The professor said
we already have a great Charlie Burnz.

1:00:46.096 --> 1:00:49.141
We don't have a great Darrell Green yet.
He was right.

1:00:50.017 --> 1:00:54.813
Anyway, working with you
and knowing you is really special to me.

1:00:54.897 --> 1:00:56.148
Oh, thank you, Darrell.

1:00:56.774 --> 1:00:59.777
Listen, while I go get one of the crew

1:00:59.860 --> 1:01:02.654
to vacuum out the smoke
you just blew up my ass,

1:01:02.738 --> 1:01:05.949
take a whack at the incredibly single guy,
see if there's something funny.

1:01:06.033 --> 1:01:08.494
- Deal.
- Good. Oh, sorry.

1:01:10.412 --> 1:01:12.247
Hello? Hi.

1:01:12.998 --> 1:01:14.875
Hi, yeah. No, I...

1:01:16.126 --> 1:01:17.211
What to wear?

1:01:18.170 --> 1:01:19.088
Oh, I don't...

1:01:20.422 --> 1:01:23.384
How vintage? That's very vintage.

1:01:23.467 --> 1:01:24.635
Yeah.

1:01:24.718 --> 1:01:27.721
No, listen. I'm at work,
so can I call you back?

1:01:28.305 --> 1:01:30.516
Okay. Bye.

1:01:33.769 --> 1:01:36.814
I'm taking a date
to my granddaughter's bat mitzvah.

1:01:37.398 --> 1:01:40.609
She's a... really fun person.
Never been to one before.

1:01:40.693 --> 1:01:42.319
Neither have I. Can I go too?

1:01:43.570 --> 1:01:46.031
I think one surprise for my family
is all they can handle.

1:01:46.115 --> 1:01:48.617
And believe me,
this young woman is full of surprises.

1:01:48.701 --> 1:01:50.577
- She sounds cool.
- Yeah, she is.

1:01:50.661 --> 1:01:52.997
She's... She's very cool.

1:01:55.499 --> 1:01:57.584
- What?
- Well...

1:01:57.668 --> 1:01:58.836
you're blushing.

1:01:58.919 --> 1:02:01.672
- Your face is a little red.
- Oh, that's...

1:02:01.755 --> 1:02:03.590
blood pressure. Yeah.

1:02:03.674 --> 1:02:05.592
Shouldn't have had the hot dog. It's...

1:02:05.676 --> 1:02:07.761
- See you in a little bit.
- Bye.

1:02:09.430 --> 1:02:14.018
Now that I'm a bat mitzvah girl,
I'd like to leave you with this one story.

1:02:14.685 --> 1:02:17.688
So I turned to Rabbi Teplis and I said:

1:02:17.771 --> 1:02:20.274
"I've been studying for years and years

1:02:20.357 --> 1:02:22.693
and I ask you:
'What is the meaning of life?'

1:02:22.776 --> 1:02:25.112
And you tell me life is a cookie?"

1:02:28.032 --> 1:02:30.617
And Rabbi Teplis looked at me and said:

1:02:30.701 --> 1:02:32.077
"You mean it isn't?"

1:02:37.082 --> 1:02:39.626
So anyways, to my parents,

1:02:39.710 --> 1:02:41.754
I love you so much.

1:02:43.005 --> 1:02:44.798
You've given me everything I have,

1:02:44.882 --> 1:02:47.468
and I wouldn't be here without you.

1:02:48.260 --> 1:02:50.888
Thank you so much. I love you.

1:02:51.722 --> 1:02:54.391
<i>Mazel tov!</i>

1:03:01.148 --> 1:03:03.484
Let's get Lindsay up in the chair!

1:03:05.736 --> 1:03:07.863
One, two, three!

1:03:10.032 --> 1:03:12.159
Look out. Here comes Mom!

1:03:12.242 --> 1:03:13.869
Up in the air, Francine.

1:03:14.953 --> 1:03:17.998
Bend your knees, boys.
Here comes Papa Charlie!

1:03:20.668 --> 1:03:22.211
Mazel tov!

1:03:25.172 --> 1:03:26.256
Come on. Sit down.

1:03:30.678 --> 1:03:32.638
This is amazing!

1:03:32.721 --> 1:03:34.807
That's it, God. I'm converted!

1:03:46.944 --> 1:03:47.778
Hi.

1:03:48.696 --> 1:03:51.031
I'm Francine. I'm Lindsay's mom.

1:03:51.115 --> 1:03:53.867
She is so special. You must be so proud.

1:03:53.951 --> 1:03:56.245
- Yeah.
- I'm Emma, by the way.

1:03:56.328 --> 1:03:57.997
- Oh, hi.
- Nice to meet you.

1:03:58.080 --> 1:04:02.042
- Yes, nice to meet you.
- These spare ribs are delicious!

1:04:02.126 --> 1:04:03.711
Oh, good.

1:04:03.794 --> 1:04:05.921
So how long
have you been dating my father?

1:04:06.005 --> 1:04:09.258
What? No, no, no. We're just friends.

1:04:10.009 --> 1:04:10.843
I'm sure.

1:04:10.926 --> 1:04:12.928
No. He's just really nice to me.

1:04:13.679 --> 1:04:14.930
And I just love his writing.

1:04:17.099 --> 1:04:19.226
Okay. So...

1:04:19.309 --> 1:04:22.062
So, what do you do, Emma?
For a living, I mean.

1:04:22.146 --> 1:04:23.063
I'm a singer.

1:04:24.481 --> 1:04:26.567
Anything I might be familiar with?

1:04:26.650 --> 1:04:27.484
No.

1:04:28.068 --> 1:04:32.614
But we got a whole bunch of videos
that are blowing up on Instagram.

1:04:33.657 --> 1:04:36.076
- Cool.
- You should come check us out.

1:04:36.160 --> 1:04:38.454
- We perform all over the city.
- Where?

1:04:39.538 --> 1:04:41.915
- Mostly underground.
- Like clubs?

1:04:42.833 --> 1:04:45.502
Sometimes, but more so subway stations.

1:04:45.586 --> 1:04:49.631
Like Columbus Circle,
Union Square, Penn Station.

1:04:49.715 --> 1:04:52.217
You gotta check us out. You know what?

1:04:52.301 --> 1:04:55.387
I'm gonna get me some more ribs
because I love meat.

1:04:55.471 --> 1:04:57.681
Anything I could pet, I eat.

1:05:12.279 --> 1:05:13.113
Lindsay...

1:05:13.864 --> 1:05:17.868
I have to tell you how proud I am of you
that you wanted to have this bat mitzvah.

1:05:18.702 --> 1:05:20.537
And I wanna give you something.

1:05:25.959 --> 1:05:27.002
This...

1:05:27.544 --> 1:05:29.588
This was your Grandma Carrie's.

1:05:31.590 --> 1:05:32.925
And now it's yours.

1:05:35.177 --> 1:05:36.637
Put your hair back.

1:05:36.720 --> 1:05:38.180
See if I can...

1:05:39.014 --> 1:05:41.058
Good. Oh, it looks perfect.

1:05:41.141 --> 1:05:43.227
- It's really pretty.
- Yeah.

1:05:43.894 --> 1:05:45.270
I'm giving you this...

1:05:45.979 --> 1:05:48.273
because today is the first big step...

1:05:49.149 --> 1:05:50.693
with so many more to come.

1:05:51.819 --> 1:05:54.655
And I'll be there for you for all of that.

1:05:56.281 --> 1:05:59.076
And I can't wait
to see who you're gonna become.

1:06:01.203 --> 1:06:02.538
I love you.

1:06:03.914 --> 1:06:04.915
I love you too.

1:06:06.583 --> 1:06:07.835
Thank you, Papa.

1:06:12.548 --> 1:06:16.260
Hey, Dad, by the way...
I got that job I was telling you about.

1:06:17.511 --> 1:06:18.512
What job?

1:06:19.638 --> 1:06:20.931
The building in Union Square.

1:06:21.932 --> 1:06:24.143
Yeah. Anyway, they love my design.

1:06:24.226 --> 1:06:26.812
Great. Isn't that great?

1:06:26.895 --> 1:06:29.690
Good going, kid. Come here.
Come here. Come here.

1:06:31.775 --> 1:06:35.279
That's great, huh?
You know, Rex is an architect.

1:06:35.362 --> 1:06:38.991
I know. Anyone who's born in a museum
is bound to be smart.

1:06:39.074 --> 1:06:41.994
- He told you about that?
- Yeah, he's very proud of you.

1:06:44.496 --> 1:06:47.249
- And this is her first bat mitzvah.
- What do you think so far?

1:06:47.333 --> 1:06:49.585
- It's okay so far.
- Just okay?

1:06:49.668 --> 1:06:54.048
In the beginning, it was really hot
with the dancing and the chairs up, but-

1:06:54.131 --> 1:06:57.718
All due respect to your tribe,
but it's a little dull now.

1:06:57.801 --> 1:07:00.179
Well, the reading. It'll pick up again.

1:07:00.262 --> 1:07:02.556
Well, why don't we do something
to help a little?

1:07:02.639 --> 1:07:03.932
Where you going?

1:07:04.767 --> 1:07:06.393
Dad. Dad!

1:07:07.770 --> 1:07:09.355
Hey, hey, hey.

1:07:09.438 --> 1:07:11.774
Do you have the instrumental for...?

1:07:16.070 --> 1:07:20.032
Good evening, everybody.
My name is Emma Payge.

1:07:20.115 --> 1:07:23.744
I'm a very good friend
of Papa Charlie's, and Lindsay?

1:07:23.827 --> 1:07:26.497
Could you please come on down
to the dance floor?

1:07:27.831 --> 1:07:31.669
This is my first time ever
coming to a bat mitzvah.

1:07:31.752 --> 1:07:34.755
And I have to say,
so far, I feel so welcome.

1:07:34.838 --> 1:07:36.507
I'm having such a good time.

1:07:36.590 --> 1:07:38.509
DJ, hit that beat.

1:07:39.218 --> 1:07:41.136
And this one's for you, Lindsay.

1:07:41.220 --> 1:07:43.681
If you know the words
to the song, sing along.

1:07:43.764 --> 1:07:46.934
If you don't, I wanna see you
dancing your heart out.

1:07:47.017 --> 1:07:53.732
<i>Oh, come on
Come on, come on, come on</i>

1:07:53.816 --> 1:08:00.572
<i>Didn't I make you feel
Like you are the only man?</i>

1:08:01.699 --> 1:08:03.409
<i>Yeah, yeah</i>

1:08:05.285 --> 1:08:08.998
<i>Didn't I nearly give you everything
a woman possibly can?</i>

1:08:11.166 --> 1:08:16.130
<i>And each time I tell myself
That I think I've had enough</i>

1:08:16.213 --> 1:08:19.090
<i>But what I'm gonna show you, baby</i>

1:08:19.174 --> 1:08:21.385
<i>That a woman can be tough</i>

1:08:21.468 --> 1:08:27.683
<i>Oh, come on
Come on, come on, come on</i>

1:08:27.766 --> 1:08:28.976
<i>And take it!</i>

1:08:29.059 --> 1:08:33.063
<i>Take another little piece
Of my heart now, baby</i>

1:08:33.147 --> 1:08:34.857
<i>Oh, break it!</i>

1:08:34.940 --> 1:08:38.527
<i>Break another little piece
Of my heart, yeah, darling</i>

1:08:39.236 --> 1:08:40.528
<i>Oh, have a...!</i>

1:08:40.612 --> 1:08:44.575
<i>Have another little piece
Of my heart, yeah, baby</i>

1:08:45.576 --> 1:08:50.873
<i>You know you got it
If it makes you feel good</i>

1:08:53.334 --> 1:08:55.461
Come here, baby. Yeah.

1:08:56.586 --> 1:09:00.340
<i>You're out there on the streets
All looking good</i>

1:09:00.424 --> 1:09:04.219
<i>And baby, deep down in your heart
You know that ain't right</i>

1:09:07.181 --> 1:09:11.934
<i>Never, never, never, never,
Never hear me when I cry</i>

1:09:14.146 --> 1:09:19.026
<i>But each time I tell myself
That I can't stand the pain</i>

1:09:19.108 --> 1:09:24.156
<i>When you hold me in your arms
I'll sing it once again</i>

1:09:24.238 --> 1:09:28.202
- No. Dad, she's...
- She's fantastic. She's fantastic.

1:09:28.285 --> 1:09:30.662
<i>...come on, come on</i>

1:09:30.746 --> 1:09:31.705
<i>And take it!</i>

1:09:31.789 --> 1:09:35.834
<i>Take another little piece
