Thanks, kid.

1:24:18.300 --> 1:24:19.677
Good night, Charlie.

1:24:19.760 --> 1:24:24.390
You know, Darrell here is gonna be
a terrific writer someday.

1:24:25.766 --> 1:24:26.934
I don't know.

1:24:27.017 --> 1:24:28.018
I do.

1:24:30.020 --> 1:24:30.979
I'll see you, kid.

1:24:33.482 --> 1:24:35.776
This is a scan of your brain in February.

1:24:36.985 --> 1:24:39.154
And this is the one we just took.

1:24:43.909 --> 1:24:45.411
They look the same to me.

1:24:46.453 --> 1:24:48.163
Yes, but your symptoms are changing.

1:24:51.166 --> 1:24:53.252
If I'm right, you may have
a form of dementia

1:24:53.335 --> 1:24:55.379
called Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease.

1:24:58.382 --> 1:25:00.426
What do you mean if you're right?

1:25:05.931 --> 1:25:09.601
Only way to get
a definitive diagnosis of CJD is...

1:25:10.686 --> 1:25:12.187
post-mortem autopsy.

1:25:13.272 --> 1:25:14.106
Well...

1:25:15.774 --> 1:25:17.067
why don't we do that now?

1:25:17.151 --> 1:25:20.154
I mean, I have a lunch
but I could cancel that.

1:25:21.739 --> 1:25:23.490
What happens next?

1:25:23.574 --> 1:25:26.160
There are other medications
than the ones you're on now...

1:25:27.202 --> 1:25:30.205
that could slow this down a bit,

1:25:30.289 --> 1:25:32.291
but before too long.

1:25:38.047 --> 1:25:39.798
Before too long is how long?

1:25:42.217 --> 1:25:43.385
A year, maybe.

1:25:47.931 --> 1:25:50.309
You probably wanna start
thinking about a caregiver.

1:25:53.228 --> 1:25:54.480
A nurse?

1:25:54.563 --> 1:25:56.482
Yes, or your family.

1:25:57.358 --> 1:25:59.193
- Your son and daughter.
- Well...

1:26:00.152 --> 1:26:01.278
that's not happening.

1:26:02.321 --> 1:26:06.200
In times like this,
you should be surrounded by loved ones,

1:26:06.283 --> 1:26:09.203
or professionals
who are trained to care for you.

1:26:15.501 --> 1:26:17.795
I'll do it. I'll take care of Charlie.

1:26:17.878 --> 1:26:19.797
No, you can't. You're going away.

1:26:19.880 --> 1:26:21.340
My plans have changed.

1:26:21.423 --> 1:26:23.467
No. No, they haven't changed.

1:26:23.550 --> 1:26:25.969
She's in a band and they're supposed
to go on tour.

1:26:26.053 --> 1:26:28.055
- Nah, I don't need to do that.
- No. Yes, you do.

1:26:28.138 --> 1:26:29.640
She does need to do that.

1:26:31.392 --> 1:26:33.102
May I ask what your relationship is?

1:26:33.769 --> 1:26:35.104
- I don't know.
- I don't know.

1:26:35.187 --> 1:26:37.272
How long have you known each other?

1:26:37.356 --> 1:26:39.900
I'm guessing about six months or so.

1:26:39.983 --> 1:26:41.652
Are you boyfriend and girlfriend?

1:26:44.780 --> 1:26:45.614
Are we?

1:26:46.573 --> 1:26:48.993
How would you define
boyfriend and girlfriend?

1:26:49.076 --> 1:26:51.787
Well, are you having sexual relations?

1:26:51.870 --> 1:26:53.664
- We spooned.
- We spooned.

1:26:56.291 --> 1:26:57.126
Charlie...

1:26:58.127 --> 1:26:59.461
what about your kids?

1:27:00.379 --> 1:27:02.631
I honestly don't know
if they've ever spooned.

1:27:02.715 --> 1:27:03.799
Charlie.

1:27:04.633 --> 1:27:07.594
- This is no time for jokes.
- Yes, it is.

1:27:08.345 --> 1:27:10.597
It's the perfect time for jokes,
goddamn it.

1:27:10.681 --> 1:27:13.642
Don't try to take away my sense of humor.
I'd rather die right now.

1:27:16.061 --> 1:27:18.564
Boy, this God...
This God is a real jokester, isn't he?

1:27:18.647 --> 1:27:20.357
What a really funny God.

1:27:20.441 --> 1:27:23.569
"Hey, live your whole life
and you won't remember any of it."

1:27:24.820 --> 1:27:25.779
Fuck you!

1:27:27.156 --> 1:27:28.907
- Damn it.
- It's gonna be okay.

1:27:28.991 --> 1:27:31.035
How can this be okay?

1:27:31.118 --> 1:27:32.661
How can this be okay?

1:27:37.541 --> 1:27:39.209
My kids don't know anything.

1:27:42.046 --> 1:27:43.505
I'll tell them at the right time.

1:27:44.757 --> 1:27:45.841
Charlie.

1:27:48.052 --> 1:27:49.428
This is the right time.

1:27:52.097 --> 1:27:53.766
You can't be alone anymore.

1:27:59.646 --> 1:28:01.482
I'll take care of him till I can't.

1:28:04.985 --> 1:28:06.570
I'll write you some prescriptions.

1:28:08.655 --> 1:28:10.574
I'll let the two of you be alone a bit.

1:28:21.752 --> 1:28:22.878
What is wrong with you?

1:28:22.961 --> 1:28:25.422
- What? There's nothing wrong with me.
- You're not staying.

1:28:25.506 --> 1:28:26.882
- Yes, I am.
- No, you're not.

1:28:26.965 --> 1:28:30.052
You heard what the doc said,
it's over, okay?

1:28:30.135 --> 1:28:32.554
That's it. Please, leave me alone!

1:28:32.638 --> 1:28:34.765
- Charlie.
- Don't "Charlie" me!

1:28:36.016 --> 1:28:36.850
You have a life!

1:28:36.934 --> 1:28:38.936
You have your music, so run.

1:28:39.019 --> 1:28:42.147
Run for the hills, kid.
It's over. I'm telling you, it's over.

1:28:42.231 --> 1:28:45.651
Please, I just wanna be alone!

1:28:45.734 --> 1:28:48.320
- I'm not going anywhere.
- I don't want you to stay!

1:28:49.196 --> 1:28:52.616
You hear me? What are you staying for?

1:28:53.575 --> 1:28:56.912
What's here?
What's gonna be left? Nothing!

1:28:56.996 --> 1:28:58.622
That's not true, Charlie.

1:29:00.708 --> 1:29:02.626
I'm lost. I'm...

1:29:03.961 --> 1:29:06.714
Help, help, help. I'm lost.

1:29:07.756 --> 1:29:10.259
I'm so... I'm so lost.

1:29:11.593 --> 1:29:13.637
I'm sorry, pal. But I'm in.

1:29:14.805 --> 1:29:16.724
You wanna be with a stranger?

1:29:19.476 --> 1:29:21.979
Pretty soon everyone's
gonna be a stranger.

1:29:22.062 --> 1:29:22.980
Not me.

1:29:24.106 --> 1:29:25.566
I'm not gonna leave you.

1:29:28.318 --> 1:29:29.153
Thank you.

1:29:50.549 --> 1:29:51.425
Hi.

1:29:52.676 --> 1:29:54.303
Whose room did this used to be?

1:29:54.386 --> 1:29:55.721
Francine's.

1:29:55.804 --> 1:29:57.431
That explains the chill.

1:29:58.015 --> 1:29:59.183
Something wrong?

1:29:59.266 --> 1:30:00.434
I can't sleep.

1:30:00.517 --> 1:30:01.518
What's up?

1:30:02.561 --> 1:30:05.147
- I wrote something.
- That's good.

1:30:05.230 --> 1:30:07.399
- I wanna read it to you.
- Okay.

1:30:07.483 --> 1:30:08.650
This is my journal.

1:30:09.151 --> 1:30:11.779
I've been writing stuff
for the book in it

1:30:11.862 --> 1:30:13.947
because typing
has become a problem for me.

1:30:14.031 --> 1:30:15.407
I know.

1:30:17.868 --> 1:30:19.328
The book is called <i>For Carrie.</i>

1:30:19.953 --> 1:30:21.330
This is the dedication.

1:30:21.413 --> 1:30:24.291
A writer always dedicates the book
to somebody he loves...

1:30:24.375 --> 1:30:26.126
- I know what it means.
- Okay.

1:30:29.213 --> 1:30:30.673
"To Emma Payge.

1:30:32.049 --> 1:30:35.844
Thank you for taking my truth
and making it more interesting.

1:30:36.679 --> 1:30:39.181
I kind of love you. CB."

1:30:39.973 --> 1:30:42.142
I kind of love you too, old man.

1:30:43.435 --> 1:30:44.269
Really?

1:30:44.895 --> 1:30:46.397
Yeah. Big time.

1:30:48.232 --> 1:30:49.316
Didn't see that coming.

1:30:51.402 --> 1:30:52.695
You make me smile.

1:30:54.238 --> 1:30:55.656
Good night.

1:30:55.739 --> 1:30:56.782
Good night.

1:31:04.039 --> 1:31:04.873
Hey, Emma.

1:31:07.710 --> 1:31:09.586
I'm grateful to you that you're here.

1:31:10.629 --> 1:31:13.173
I wanna have fun. I wanna laugh.

1:31:13.257 --> 1:31:14.717
I want to not be scared.

1:31:15.342 --> 1:31:18.178
And I wanna write the book,
and I wanna do all of that with you.

1:31:18.262 --> 1:31:19.888
But you have to promise me something.

1:31:21.140 --> 1:31:22.307
When it's time...

1:31:23.976 --> 1:31:25.769
you go back out and sing.

1:31:25.853 --> 1:31:27.980
You're an artist,
and that's what you should do.

1:31:28.063 --> 1:31:29.231
Please, promise me.

1:31:30.733 --> 1:31:31.567
I promise.

1:31:32.109 --> 1:31:32.943
Good.

1:31:34.945 --> 1:31:37.031
I'm a bargain for 22 bucks,
don't you think?

1:31:37.656 --> 1:31:38.824
Hell, yeah.

1:31:41.160 --> 1:31:42.578
- Good night.
- Good night.

1:32:10.606 --> 1:32:14.068
I must've dozed off.
These new meds are making me very sleepy.

1:32:14.151 --> 1:32:16.737
I haven't taken a nap
since the Carter administration.

1:32:18.864 --> 1:32:20.491
- What do you have there?
- Nothing.

1:32:21.617 --> 1:32:22.743
Let me see.

1:32:24.203 --> 1:32:25.037
The...

1:32:25.788 --> 1:32:28.999
- It's that...
- Emma, I know what it is.

1:32:30.209 --> 1:32:33.962
I know you said get rid of it,
but it's just so beautiful.

1:32:34.046 --> 1:32:34.880
Give it to me.

1:32:47.685 --> 1:32:49.812
Carrie painted this. Yeah.

1:32:50.896 --> 1:32:55.150
See, she put her name in the bushes.
See there? In the trees.

1:32:58.737 --> 1:33:00.406
This is Lake Charlie.

1:33:00.489 --> 1:33:02.491
Lake Charlie. Where's that?

1:33:02.574 --> 1:33:06.203
That's about two hours
north of the city. Yeah.

1:33:07.997 --> 1:33:10.165
Carrie gave me a lake for my birthday.

1:33:10.249 --> 1:33:11.333
A lake?

1:33:11.417 --> 1:33:14.044
Yeah. It was actually a pond.

1:33:14.128 --> 1:33:18.048
But Pond Charlie
didn't sound as good as Lake Charlie.

1:33:18.132 --> 1:33:19.008
Wait.

1:33:19.675 --> 1:33:20.676
What?

1:33:21.885 --> 1:33:24.847
Tell me all about Lake Charlie.

1:33:26.306 --> 1:33:27.433
Okay.

1:33:29.184 --> 1:33:30.769
It's my 40th birthday.

1:33:30.853 --> 1:33:33.355
Happy birthday, Charlie Burnz.

1:33:33.439 --> 1:33:34.857
Happy birthday, Charlie.

1:33:35.441 --> 1:33:38.277
<i>We had a party outside in the garden.</i>

1:33:38.360 --> 1:33:39.987
<i>And after everybody was gone...</i>

1:33:40.696 --> 1:33:43.449
<i>Carrie shows me this photograph
of this woodsy area</i>

1:33:43.532 --> 1:33:44.908
<i>with this beautiful lake on it.</i>

1:33:44.992 --> 1:33:48.245
Happy birthday, Charlie Burnz.
This is for you.

1:33:48.746 --> 1:33:51.248
For me? What is this?
What am I looking at?

1:33:52.207 --> 1:33:54.376
It's called Lake Charlie.

1:33:54.460 --> 1:33:55.627
Lake Charlie?

1:33:55.711 --> 1:33:58.047
<i>She was always trying to get me
to stop working.</i>

1:33:58.130 --> 1:34:01.884
And just be alone with her and do nothing.

1:34:01.967 --> 1:34:06.055
And honestly the thought of doing nothing
terrified me, you know?

1:34:07.973 --> 1:34:10.434
But I loved her so much
and it meant so much to her

1:34:10.517 --> 1:34:15.064
that we'd go up there, you know,
and camp out, like, in a tent.

1:34:15.147 --> 1:34:16.732
Can you imagine me in a tent?

1:34:16.815 --> 1:34:21.320
<i>I mean, to me, the great outdoors
would be a lot better if it was indoors.</i>

1:34:21.403 --> 1:34:23.113
Good morning!

1:34:27.368 --> 1:34:31.205
That smells good.
Smells better than me.

1:34:34.249 --> 1:34:36.168
Wow... Whoa! Look what you did.

1:34:40.756 --> 1:34:42.174
- Hey, Charlie?
- Yeah?

1:34:42.800 --> 1:34:44.635
- You know what I think?
- What?

1:34:45.386 --> 1:34:48.555
- I think we need a house.
- A house?

1:34:48.639 --> 1:34:49.640
Yeah.

1:34:50.224 --> 1:34:51.642
The kids will love it up here.

1:34:52.810 --> 1:34:55.437
- Kids?
- Didn't I tell you?

1:34:57.356 --> 1:34:59.692
And that's how she told me
she was pregnant with Rex.

1:35:01.193 --> 1:35:03.529
So she went looking for a house.

1:35:03.612 --> 1:35:05.698
Wait, didn't you guys build a house?

1:35:05.781 --> 1:35:07.616
Oh, no, that's way too easy for Carrie.

1:35:07.700 --> 1:35:10.285
She scoured the countryside
then she found this little house,

1:35:10.369 --> 1:35:12.621
she bought it and lifted it up,

1:35:12.705 --> 1:35:15.582
put it on a flatbed truck
and she drove it to Lake Charlie.

1:35:15.666 --> 1:35:18.377
Got a house, Charlie Burnz!

1:35:20.421 --> 1:35:21.755
Thank you.

1:35:21.839 --> 1:35:23.924
<i>So we put in a new foundation,</i>

1:35:24.008 --> 1:35:26.510
<i>plopped the house down on it,
renovated it,</i>

1:35:26.593 --> 1:35:29.096
<i>painted it up,
made it a little bit bigger.</i>

1:35:29.179 --> 1:35:30.597
<i>It was our happy place.</i>

1:35:30.681 --> 1:35:33.892
Dad, come on! Let's go play.
Daddy, come on!

1:35:33.976 --> 1:35:35.019
<i>She was right.</i>

1:35:35.102 --> 1:35:37.229
Daddy, come on. Are you playing or not?

1:35:37.312 --> 1:35:38.856
The kids loved it.

1:35:40.065 --> 1:35:42.901
Now I know why
you didn't wanna hang the picture.

1:35:44.653 --> 1:35:45.779
No, you don't.

1:35:48.615 --> 1:35:50.743
I'm tired. I can't talk anymore.

1:35:50.826 --> 1:35:54.121
Come on, Charlie. Please?
Don't take this with you.

1:35:54.997 --> 1:35:56.790
I'm not going anywhere yet.

1:36:00.669 --> 1:36:05.049
Okay. My first Broadway play,
<i>It's My Time,</i>

1:36:05.132 --> 1:36:06.592
<i>opened up at the Belasco Theatre.</i>

1:36:07.051 --> 1:36:10.637
<i>Reviews were terrific, business was great,
but that wasn't enough for me.</i>

1:36:10.721 --> 1:36:12.806
<i>The star was an actor named Jerry Orbach,</i>

1:36:12.890 --> 1:36:15.392
<i>and there was this one speech
late in the second act.</i>

1:36:15.476 --> 1:36:18.354
<i>It never landed right. It drove me crazy.</i>

1:36:18.437 --> 1:36:20.898
All I wanted was one show
that was just perfect.

1:36:26.320 --> 1:36:29.698
Things were tense...

1:36:30.949 --> 1:36:32.409
between the two of us.

1:36:33.369 --> 1:36:34.995
<i>I'd been working so much.</i>

1:36:35.079 --> 1:36:36.163
What are we doing?

1:36:36.246 --> 1:36:39.833
<i>I'd been on the road for four months
with the play before it came to Broadway.</i>

1:36:39.917 --> 1:36:42.628
<i>And everybody was looking forward
to spending some time together</i>

1:36:42.711 --> 1:36:45.005
<i>at Lake Charlie, and what was I doing?</i>

1:36:45.089 --> 1:36:47.800
<i>I was rewriting a play
that was already a hit.</i>

1:36:47.883 --> 1:36:50.803
Charlie, we have to go right now.

1:36:51.303 --> 1:36:53.722
Jefferson will be awful.
I don't like driving in the dark.

1:36:53.806 --> 1:36:56.684
My mom's got the kids there waiting.
We should have left an hour ago.

1:36:56.767 --> 1:36:59.311
I had to rewrite a speech for Jerry.
It wasn't landing right.

1:36:59.395 --> 1:37:01.355
Great. Okay. That's just great.

1:37:01.438 --> 1:37:03.774
He's reading it.
I wanna make sure it's okay with him.

1:37:03.857 --> 1:37:07.861
You wanna make sure it's okay with him?
With him? How about with me?

1:37:07.945 --> 1:37:10.698
How about your kids
who you haven't seen for months?

1:37:10.781 --> 1:37:12.366
You promised me. You promised us.

1:37:12.449 --> 1:37:15.619
Stop yelling. Five minutes,
I promise. I'll be right in and right out.

1:37:15.703 --> 1:37:18.038
- The kids are waiting.
- I understand. I'll be right out.

1:37:18.122 --> 1:37:20.290
The people are in line,
the show goes up in an hour.

1:37:20.374 --> 1:37:22.126
- Five minutes?
- Yeah. Yeah.

1:37:22.209 --> 1:37:24.962
I know you're upset,
but I hate when you get like this.

1:37:25.045 --> 1:37:28.173
If you're not back in five minutes,
I'm leaving without you.

1:37:28.257 --> 1:37:32.136
I heard you, okay? I heard you.
Goddamn it.

1:37:36.306 --> 1:37:40.144
<i>It took 15 minutes.
When I came out she was gone.</i>

1:37:40.978 --> 1:37:46.316
<i>I was angry. So I watched the show,
that damn speech still didn't land right.</i>

1:37:46.400 --> 1:37:49.278
<i>I had a couple of drinks with Jerry
and then I came back here...</i>

1:37:50.988 --> 1:37:53.949
And the next thing I remember
is flashing lights.

1:37:55.117 --> 1:38:00.789
And a policeman in the doorway
asking me my name over and over again.

1:38:02.458 --> 1:38:05.044
And I'm thinking if I don't answer him,

1:38:05.127 --> 1:38:08.380
then maybe what he's about
to tell me didn't happen.

1:38:16.597 --> 1:38:20.768
He told me Carrie was driving
on this dark road right near the house.

1:38:20.851 --> 1:38:22.853
She came to this fork in the road,

1:38:24.104 --> 1:38:27.900
and some kid loaded on pills
driving a Jeep ran the stop sign.

1:38:30.486 --> 1:38:31.945
And he hit her head-on.

1:38:33.614 --> 1:38:34.907
She died instantly.

1:38:36.075 --> 1:38:37.868
Kid walked away without a scratch.

1:38:39.870 --> 1:38:42.748
The last time I saw that beautiful face
she was mad at me.

1:38:45.501 --> 1:38:48.379
That's why I can't look
at that picture anymore.

1:38:49.171 --> 1:38:52.341
It makes me remember
the one thing I want to forget.

1:39:00.599 --> 1:39:01.558
I'm sorry.

1:39:06.814 --> 1:39:07.940
Me too.

1:39:17.032 --> 1:39:20.244
- You need anything from the store?
- Wonton soup.

1:39:20.327 --> 1:39:22.788
I'd like to shampoo my hair.
It's getting a little greasy...

1:39:22.871 --> 1:39:25.124
- Charlie.
- What?

1:39:26.542 --> 1:39:30.379
I'm just kidding. I'm okay.
I promise. Thanks.

1:39:30.462 --> 1:39:31.422
Good.

1:39:31.505 --> 1:39:35.175
Hey, I was thinking, you know
what we can do some day? It could be fun.

1:39:35.718 --> 1:39:39.972
Ever been to Madame Tussaud's Wax Museum?
You ever been there?

1:39:40.055 --> 1:39:42.599
It's a lot of fun.
It's pretty amazing what they do.

1:39:48.272 --> 1:39:50.774
Okay. Sure.

1:40:09.376 --> 1:40:14.298
You're back already?
Okay. Coming, coming, coming.

1:40:17.926 --> 1:40:19.678
- Hi!
- Hi.

1:40:19.762 --> 1:40:22.890
Come on in. Come on in.
This is a surprise.

1:40:22.973 --> 1:40:26.268
What's the matter?
You look very upset. What's wrong?

1:40:26.352 --> 1:40:28.103
I had a fight with my mom.

1:40:28.187 --> 1:40:29.897
She said you were
drunk and embarrassing.

1:40:29.980 --> 1:40:32.483
I said you could never be.
You were funny on the show.

1:40:32.566 --> 1:40:35.110
Why did she keep you away from me?
She said something awful.

1:40:35.194 --> 1:40:37.529
- Does she know where you are?
- She thinks I'm at school.

1:40:37.613 --> 1:40:39.156
- How did you get here?
- Uber.

1:40:39.239 --> 1:40:42.159
- We should tell her you're here.
- No! She'll be so mad at me.

1:40:42.242 --> 1:40:45.704
- But Lindsay...
- Please. I just have to know if it's true.

1:40:45.788 --> 1:40:47.289
Is what true?

1:40:49.249 --> 1:40:52.127
She said it was because of you
that I don't have a grandma.

1:40:52.920 --> 1:40:54.380
She said that to you?

1:40:54.463 --> 1:40:57.216
I overheard her
on the phone with Uncle Rex.

1:40:59.468 --> 1:41:00.844
No, Lindsay, no.

1:41:01.595 --> 1:41:02.846
Okay.

1:41:06.975 --> 1:41:08.852
Lindsay never made it to school, Rex.

1:41:08.936 --> 1:41:11.897
She used my Uber account
and guess where she took it to.

1:41:13.399 --> 1:41:18.737
I got your wonton soup but the chef said
that you need to use extra conditioner...

1:41:19.780 --> 1:41:21.073
Charlie!

1:41:22.199 --> 1:41:26.120
I got some short ribs, it'll be so good.

1:41:27.371 --> 1:41:28.247
Charlie?

1:41:29.707 --> 1:41:32.292
Charlie? Charlie!

1:41:34.294 --> 1:41:38.424
Where are you, old man?
Charlie, stop playing.

1:41:38.507 --> 1:41:40.884
Hey. Where is she?

1:41:40.968 --> 1:41:44.138
- How'd you get in here?
- We grew up here. Where is she?

1:41:44.221 --> 1:41:45.389
- Who?
- My daughter Lindsay.

1:41:45.472 --> 1:41:46.849
And our father. Where's our dad?

1:41:46.932 --> 1:41:48.183
- Lindsay!
- Dad!

1:41:48.267 --> 1:41:51.061
Nobody's here. I just got home myself.

1:41:51.145 --> 1:41:52.896
- Home?
- Do you live here?

1:41:52.980 --> 1:41:55.899
- I moved in a few days ago.
- Oh, lovely.

1:41:55.983 --> 1:41:58.068
- Your dad needs me right now.
- I bet he does.

1:41:59.111 --> 1:42:01.405
You might want
to rethink your attitude, Francine.

1:42:01.989 --> 1:42:04.283
What is this? What is all this about?

1:42:04.783 --> 1:42:06.994
Research for a project he's working on.

1:42:07.077 --> 1:42:09.872
- With our names under the pictures?
- He doesn't know who we are?

1:42:09.955 --> 1:42:11.040
Not all the time.

1:42:12.458 --> 1:42:13.959
Your father's sick.

1:42:14.710 --> 1:42:17.796
He has a form of dementia.
And it's getting worse.

1:42:18.964 --> 1:42:20.549
He can't be alone anymore.

1:42:21.425 --> 1:42:23.927
That's why I moved in, Francine.

1:42:24.011 --> 1:42:28.599
I'm his friend. He's writing a book about
your family and I'm helping him finish it.

1:42:29.725 --> 1:42:31.977
- I can't believe this.
- We had no idea.

1:42:32.061 --> 1:42:34.104
Because you're too busy
being pissed at him.

1:42:35.064 --> 1:42:38.317
Pretty soon before you know it,
he's not gonna know who you are.

1:42:38.400 --> 1:42:39.818
But you'll remember him.

1:42:40.444 --> 1:42:44.573
He's done a very good job at beating
himself up without you guys piling on.

1:42:44.656 --> 1:42:46.492
You were very happy once.

1:42:46.575 --> 1:42:49.203
It can happen again if you let it.

1:42:50.329 --> 1:42:53.374
- How do we find them?
- I put a GPS on his phone.

1:42:53.457 --> 1:42:55.292
Okay. Let me see.

1:42:59.088 --> 1:43:02.132
- No. No, no, no.
- It's here. It's here.

1:43:03.217 --> 1:43:05.177
Where the hell are they?

1:43:05.260 --> 1:43:07.721
If she's still using my Uber account,
we can find them.

1:43:31.996 --> 1:43:33.372
I cannot believe this.

1:43:33.455 --> 1:43:36.625
- Hey. What's wrong?
- Longer trip than I thought.

1:43:36.709 --> 1:43:39.211
You give five star. I accept nothing less.

1:43:39.294 --> 1:43:40.671
Is this the best way to go?

1:43:42.381 --> 1:43:43.966
This is all my fault.

1:43:44.049 --> 1:43:46.260
She overheard what I said to you.
We got in a fight...

1:43:46.343 --> 1:43:49.471
- She heard that?
- Yes. I know. I'm sorry, okay?

1:43:49.555 --> 1:43:53.183
- What if he does something crazy?
- What's he gonna do, Francine?

1:43:53.267 --> 1:43:57.855
- What's gonna happen?
- He loves Lindsay. Nothing will happen.

1:43:57.938 --> 1:43:59.440
How can you be so sure?

1:44:00.107 --> 1:44:01.650
I know him.

1:44:09.616 --> 1:44:13.287
Papa! Where are you going? Come back!

1:44:17.458 --> 1:44:21.754
- Please stop!
- Hey, what about my five stars?!

1:44:25.007 --> 1:44:28.135
Oh, God! Lindsay, honey, are you okay?

1:44:28.218 --> 1:44:29.887
Papa Charlie ran away!

1:44:29.970 --> 1:44:32.848
He told the driver to pull over,
jumped out of the car and ran.

1:44:32.931 --> 1:44:34.725
I'm scared. I'm in the woods.

1:44:34.808 --> 1:44:37.644
Lindsay, don't worry. Look around.
Can you see anything?

1:44:37.728 --> 1:44:38.854
I can see the road.

1:44:38.937 --> 1:44:41.774
Go there. Go to the road.
We're gonna find you.

1:44:49.198 --> 1:44:51.075
Mom! Mom!

1:44:54.036 --> 1:44:55.287
Lindsay!

1:44:56.830 --> 1:44:58.040
Sweetheart.

1:45:01.168 --> 1:45:02.670
Come on. Back in the car.

1:45:02.753 --> 1:45:07.091
- Oh, my God. Rex.
- I know. Let's find him.

1:45:16.850 --> 1:45:18.018
Dad?

1:45:18.602 --> 1:45:19.937
- Papa Charlie?
- Dad?

1:45:20.020 --> 1:45:22.022
- Charlie?
- Papa Charlie?

1:45:22.106 --> 1:45:25.693
No, Dad. No. Please, Dad. Dad?

1:45:25.776 --> 1:45:27.444
- Charlie?
- Dad?

1:45:29.697 --> 1:45:31.240
Charlie!

1:45:31.323 --> 1:45:32.408
Papa Charlie!

1:45:32.491 --> 1:45:34.326
Charlie!

1:45:35.995 --> 1:45:39.832
- Dad! Dad!
- Charlie!

1:45:39.915 --> 1:45:42.584
- Papa Charlie!
- Dad!

1:45:42.668 --> 1:45:45.254
- Charlie!
- Dad!

1:45:45.337 --> 1:45:47.840
Papa Charlie, where are you?

1:45:53.387 --> 1:45:54.513
Charlie!

1:45:56.974 --> 1:45:58.142
Charlie.

1:46:02.521 --> 1:46:03.856
- Hey.
- Hey.

1:46:08.068 --> 1:46:11.864
- Hey. You're okay?
- My feet are wet.

1:46:11.947 --> 1:46:13.198
Mine are too.

1:46:14.533 --> 1:46:16.160
Are you okay? You look so upset.

1:46:16.243 --> 1:46:18.078
I'm just happy to see you.

1:46:18.162 --> 1:46:19.455
Dad.

1:46:22.374 --> 1:46:23.834
What are you doing here?

1:46:25.044 --> 1:46:26.253
Hi.

1:46:27.421 --> 1:46:31.592
I wanted to show Lindsay Lake Charlie.

1:46:32.426 --> 1:46:34.136
This is our happy place.

1:46:35.554 --> 1:46:37.681
See, on sunsets we stand right here.

1:46:38.307 --> 1:46:44.438
And we'd watch the sun go down there
and "Bye-bye sun. Bye-bye sun."

1:46:44.521 --> 1:46:45.647
Somebody would say that.

1:46:45.731 --> 1:46:47.274
That was me, Dad.

1:46:48.567 --> 1:46:50.819
- I said that.
- Yeah.

1:46:57.076 --> 1:46:59.286
- I'm sorry about your mother.
- No.

1:46:59.370 --> 1:47:02.665
- Dad, you don't have to.
- No, I have to. I have to, Rex.

1:47:03.165 --> 1:47:05.542
Let me finish
because I'm running out of words.

1:47:09.963 --> 1:47:12.341
Francine, I was not
the reason your mom died.

1:47:14.301 --> 1:47:17.054
That kid who ran the stop sign
was the reason your mom died.

1:47:18.180 --> 1:47:21.517
And I adored her so much.
I loved your mother so much.

1:47:21.600 --> 1:47:23.977
And she died mad at me.

1:47:26.271 --> 1:47:28.691
I can't leave here
knowing that you're mad at me too.

1:47:31.026 --> 1:47:36.156
I can't undo it. I can't undo it.
There's no rewrites this time.

1:47:36.240 --> 1:47:39.702
Come on. Relax. Relax your hands.

1:47:40.869 --> 1:47:42.830
No more fists. Relax your hands.

1:47:47.793 --> 1:47:51.338
Dad. Why didn't you tell us?

1:47:53.841 --> 1:47:56.719
Because I didn't know how.

1:47:59.096 --> 1:48:00.055
And I was scared.

1:48:01.432 --> 1:48:02.349
Of what?

1:48:03.225 --> 1:48:05.978
That maybe you wouldn't care.

1:48:06.061 --> 1:48:07.354
Oh, Dad.

1:48:10.315 --> 1:48:11.775
Forgive me. Please.

1:48:12.943 --> 1:48:15.237
Forgive me so I could forgive myself.

1:48:15.320 --> 1:48:18.073
Because the sight of
your angry eyes keeps me up at night

1:48:18.157 --> 1:48:21.243
and gives me the sweats,
and there's no more time for that.

1:48:21.327 --> 1:48:23.912
There's no more time. I'm here today.

1:48:23.996 --> 1:48:26.123
Daddy, I'm so sorry.

1:48:26.206 --> 1:48:30.919
Franny, it's okay. It's okay.
I understand. I understand.

1:48:31.462 --> 1:48:35.215
- I love you, Pop.
- Is there room for me?

1:48:35.299 --> 1:48:37.468
- Come here, sweetie.
- I love you too, you know?

1:48:40.471 --> 1:48:42.598
Emma. Emma. Come here.

1:48:47.853 --> 1:48:50.397
Oh, God. What a long time between hugs.

1:49:00.866 --> 1:49:04.161
Mom was always inventing days
for the kids.

1:49:04.244 --> 1:49:06.330
Kids loved "Backwards Day" the best.

1:49:06.413 --> 1:49:08.791
We'd have dinner for breakfast
and breakfast for dinner.

1:49:08.874 --> 1:49:10.793
No, Pop. It was "Upside-down Day."

1:49:10.876 --> 1:49:14.046
God, I love that.
We would have cake for breakfast.

1:49:14.129 --> 1:49:15.464
- Can we do that?
- Yeah.

1:49:15.547 --> 1:49:17.633
Will you do it with us,
Papa Charlie and Emma?

1:49:17.716 --> 1:49:21.637
- Absolutely.
- Anything for you. Is it upside-down day?

1:49:21.720 --> 1:49:23.222
Yeah. Upside-down day.

1:49:24.014 --> 1:49:25.933
I got it. Upside-down day is great.

1:49:26.016 --> 1:49:28.060
- Yeah?
- This will be really good.

1:49:28.143 --> 1:49:29.228
Okay.

1:49:33.315 --> 1:49:37.611
Hey, Rex, tell them the story about
when Dad was barbecuing outside

1:49:37.695 --> 1:49:40.114
he was making all these hot dogs
and a bear came.

1:49:40.698 --> 1:49:42.449
That's a really good story.

1:49:42.533 --> 1:49:48.038
- Okay, so I think it was July 4th.
- Dad loves 4th of Julys.

1:49:53.002 --> 1:49:54.420
It's beautiful here.

1:50:00.175 --> 1:50:01.510
Are you okay?

1:50:05.889 --> 1:50:06.807
I'm here.

1:50:52.353 --> 1:50:53.812
Come on. Sun's going down.

1:50:55.939 --> 1:50:59.026
It's going. Come on,
he's not gonna wait for us.

1:51:03.155 --> 1:51:05.699
Come on. Don't wanna miss it.

1:51:09.119 --> 1:51:10.746
This is gonna be a beauty.

1:51:11.664 --> 1:51:13.666
Okay, that looks so beautiful.

1:52:06.260 --> 1:52:07.386
Bye-bye, Sun.

1:52:33.203 --> 1:52:34.830
Goodbye, old man.
